112#define SNAP_VERTICAL(func, y) ((func ((double)((y) - DESKTOP_PAD_VERTICAL) / SNAP_SIZE_Y) * SNAP_SIZE_Y) + DESKTOP_PAD_VERTICAL)

283static void
284icon_free (CajaIcon *icon)
285{
286 /* Destroy this canvas item; the parent will unref it. */
287 eel_canvas_item_destroy (EEL_CANVAS_ITEM (icon->item));
288 g_free (icon);
289}
290
291static gboolean
292icon_is_positioned (const CajaIcon *icon)
293{
294 return icon->x != ICON_UNPOSITIONED_VALUE && icon->y != ICON_UNPOSITIONED_VALUE;
295}
296
297/* x, y are the top-left coordinates of the icon. */
298static void
299icon_set_position_full (CajaIcon *icon,
300 double x, double y,
301 gboolean force)
302{
303 CajaIconContainer *container;
304 int x1, x2, y1, y2;
305 EelDRect icon_bounds;
306 GdkDisplay *display;
307
308 if (!force && icon->x == x && icon->y == y)
309 {
310 return;
311 }
312
313 container = CAJA_ICON_CONTAINER (EEL_CANVAS_ITEM (icon->item)->canvas);
314
315 if (icon == get_icon_being_renamed (container))
316 {
317 end_renaming_mode (container, TRUE);
318 }
319 double pixels_per_unit;
320 int container_left, container_top, container_right, container_bottom;
321 int container_x, container_y, container_width, container_height;
322 int item_width, item_height;
323 int height_above, width_left;
324 int min_x, max_x, min_y, max_y;
325 if (caja_icon_container_get_is_fixed_size (container))
326 {
327 /*Use the older and well tested code in x11*/
328 display = gdk_screen_get_display (gdk_screen_get_default());
329 if (GDK_IS_X11_DISPLAY (display))
330 {
331 int scale;
332
333 /* FIXME: This should be:
334
335 container_x = GTK_WIDGET (container)->allocation.x;
336 container_width = GTK_WIDGET (container)->allocation.width;
337 container_height = GTK_WIDGET (container)->allocation.height;
338
339 But for some reason the widget allocation is sometimes not done
340 at startup, and the allocation is then only 45x60. which is
341 really bad.
342
343 For now, we have a cheesy workaround:
344 */
345 scale = gtk_widget_get_scale_factor (GTK_WIDGET (container));
346 container_x = 0;
347 container_y = 0;
348 container_width = WidthOfScreen (gdk_x11_screen_get_xscreen (gdk_screen_get_default ())) / scale - container_x
349 - container->details->left_margin
350 - container->details->right_margin;
351 container_height = HeightOfScreen (gdk_x11_screen_get_xscreen (gdk_screen_get_default ())) / scale - container_y
352 - container->details->top_margin
353 - container->details->bottom_margin;
354 }
355 else
356 {
357 GdkWindow *window;
358 GdkMonitor *monitor;
359 GdkRectangle workarea = {0};
360
361 window = gtk_widget_get_window (GTK_WIDGET(container));
362 monitor = gdk_display_get_monitor_at_window (gdk_display_get_default(), window);
363 gdk_monitor_get_workarea(monitor, &workarea);
364 container_x = 0;
365 container_y = 0;
366 container_width = workarea.width - container_x
367 - container->details->left_margin
368 - container->details->right_margin;
369 container_height = workarea.height - container_y
370 - container->details->top_margin
371 - container->details->bottom_margin;
372 }
373
374 pixels_per_unit = EEL_CANVAS (container)->pixels_per_unit;
375 /* Clip the position of the icon within our desktop bounds */
376 container_left = container_x / pixels_per_unit;
377 container_top = container_y / pixels_per_unit;
378 container_right = container_left + container_width / pixels_per_unit;
379 container_bottom = container_top + container_height / pixels_per_unit;
380
381 icon_get_bounding_box (icon, &x1, &y1, &x2, &y2,
382 BOUNDS_USAGE_FOR_ENTIRE_ITEM);
383 item_width = x2 - x1;
384 item_height = y2 - y1;
385
386 icon_bounds = caja_icon_canvas_item_get_icon_rectangle (icon->item);
387
388 /* determine icon rectangle relative to item rectangle */
389 height_above = icon_bounds.y0 - y1;
390 width_left = icon_bounds.x0 - x1;
391
392 min_x = container_left + DESKTOP_PAD_HORIZONTAL + width_left;
393 max_x = container_right - DESKTOP_PAD_HORIZONTAL - item_width + width_left;
394 x = CLAMP (x, min_x, max_x);
395
396 min_y = container_top + height_above + DESKTOP_PAD_VERTICAL;
397 max_y = container_bottom - DESKTOP_PAD_VERTICAL - item_height + height_above;
398 y = CLAMP (y, min_y, max_y);
399 }
400
401 if (icon->x == ICON_UNPOSITIONED_VALUE)
402 {
403 icon->x = 0;
404 }
405 if (icon->y == ICON_UNPOSITIONED_VALUE)
406 {
407 icon->y = 0;
408 }
409
410 eel_canvas_item_move (EEL_CANVAS_ITEM (icon->item),
411 x - icon->x,
412 y - icon->y);
413
414 icon->x = x;
415 icon->y = y;
416}
417
418static void
419icon_set_position (CajaIcon *icon,
420 double x, double y)
421{
422 icon_set_position_full (icon, x, y, FALSE);
423}
424
425static void
426icon_get_size (CajaIconContainer *container,
427 CajaIcon *icon,
428 guint *size)
429{
430 if (size != NULL)
431 {
432 *size = MAX (caja_get_icon_size_for_zoom_level (container->details->zoom_level)
433 * icon->scale, CAJA_ICON_SIZE_SMALLEST);
434 }
435}
436
437/* The icon_set_size function is used by the stretching user
438 * interface, which currently stretches in a way that keeps the aspect
439 * ratio. Later we might have a stretching interface that stretches Y
440 * separate from X and we will change this around.
441 */
442static void
443icon_set_size (CajaIconContainer *container,
444 CajaIcon *icon,
445 guint icon_size,
446 gboolean snap,
447 gboolean update_position)
448{
449 guint old_size;
450 double scale;
451
452 icon_get_size (container, icon, &old_size);
453 if (icon_size == old_size)
454 {
455 return;
456 }
457
458 scale = (double) icon_size /
459 caja_get_icon_size_for_zoom_level
460 (container->details->zoom_level);
461 caja_icon_container_move_icon (container, icon,
462 icon->x, icon->y,
463 scale, FALSE,
464 snap, update_position);
465}
466
467static void
468icon_raise (CajaIcon *icon)
469{
470 EelCanvasItem *item, *band;
471
472 item = EEL_CANVAS_ITEM (icon->item);
473 band = CAJA_ICON_CONTAINER (item->canvas)->details->rubberband_info.selection_rectangle;
474
475 eel_canvas_item_send_behind (item, band);
476}

478static void
479emit_stretch_started (CajaIconContainer *container, CajaIcon *icon)
480{
481 g_signal_emit (container,
482 signals[ICON_STRETCH_STARTED], 0,
483 icon->data);
484}
485
486static void
487emit_stretch_ended (CajaIconContainer *container, CajaIcon *icon)
488{
489 g_signal_emit (container,
490 signals[ICON_STRETCH_ENDED], 0,
491 icon->data);
492}
493
494static void
495icon_toggle_selected (CajaIconContainer *container,
496 CajaIcon *icon)
497{
498 end_renaming_mode (container, TRUE);
499
500 icon->is_selected = !icon->is_selected;
501 eel_canvas_item_set (EEL_CANVAS_ITEM (icon->item),
502 "highlighted_for_selection", (gboolean) icon->is_selected,
503 NULL);
504
505 /* If the icon is deselected, then get rid of the stretch handles.
506 * No harm in doing the same if the item is newly selected.
507 */
508 if (icon == container->details->stretch_icon)
509 {
510 container->details->stretch_icon = NULL;
511 caja_icon_canvas_item_set_show_stretch_handles (icon->item, FALSE);
512 /* snap the icon if necessary */
513 if (container->details->keep_aligned)
514 {
515 caja_icon_container_move_icon (container,
516 icon,
517 icon->x, icon->y,
518 icon->scale,
519 FALSE, TRUE, TRUE);
520 }
521
522 emit_stretch_ended (container, icon);
523 }
524
525 /* Raise each newly-selected icon to the front as it is selected. */
526 if (icon->is_selected)
527 {
528 icon_raise (icon);
529 }
530}
531
532/* Select an icon. Return TRUE if selection has changed. */
533static gboolean
534icon_set_selected (CajaIconContainer *container,
535 CajaIcon *icon,
536 gboolean select)
537{
538 g_assert (select == FALSE || select == TRUE);
539 g_assert (icon->is_selected == FALSE || icon->is_selected == TRUE);
540
541 if (select == icon->is_selected)
542 {
543 return FALSE;
544 }
545
546 icon_toggle_selected (container, icon);
547 g_assert (select == icon->is_selected);
548 return TRUE;
549}
550
551static inline void
552icon_get_bounding_box (CajaIcon *icon,
553 int *x1_return, int *y1_return,
554 int *x2_return, int *y2_return,
555 CajaIconCanvasItemBoundsUsage usage)
556{
557 double x1, y1, x2, y2;
558
559 if (usage == BOUNDS_USAGE_FOR_DISPLAY)
560 {
561 eel_canvas_item_get_bounds (EEL_CANVAS_ITEM (icon->item),
562 &x1, &y1, &x2, &y2);
563 }
564 else if (usage == BOUNDS_USAGE_FOR_LAYOUT)
565 {
566 caja_icon_canvas_item_get_bounds_for_layout (icon->item,
567 &x1, &y1, &x2, &y2);
568 }
569 else if (usage == BOUNDS_USAGE_FOR_ENTIRE_ITEM)
570 {
571 caja_icon_canvas_item_get_bounds_for_entire_item (icon->item,
572 &x1, &y1, &x2, &y2);
573 }
574 else
575 {
576 g_assert_not_reached ();
577 }
578
579 if (x1_return != NULL)
580 {
581 *x1_return = x1;
582 }
583
584 if (y1_return != NULL)
585 {
586 *y1_return = y1;
587 }
588
589 if (x2_return != NULL)
590 {
591 *x2_return = x2;
592 }
593
594 if (y2_return != NULL)
595 {
596 *y2_return = y2;
597 }
598}
599
600/* Utility functions for CajaIconContainer. */
601
602gboolean
603caja_icon_container_scroll (CajaIconContainer *container,
604 int delta_x, int delta_y)
605{
606 GtkAdjustment *hadj, *vadj;
607 int old_h_value, old_v_value;
608
609 hadj = gtk_scrollable_get_hadjustment (GTK_SCROLLABLE (container));
610 vadj = gtk_scrollable_get_vadjustment (GTK_SCROLLABLE (container));
611
612 /* Store the old ajustment values so we can tell if we
613 * ended up actually scrolling. We may not have in a case
614 * where the resulting value got pinned to the adjustment
615 * min or max.
616 */
617 old_h_value = gtk_adjustment_get_value (hadj);
618 old_v_value = gtk_adjustment_get_value (vadj);
619
620 gtk_adjustment_set_value (hadj, gtk_adjustment_get_value (hadj) + delta_x);
621 gtk_adjustment_set_value (vadj, gtk_adjustment_get_value (vadj) + delta_y);
622
623 /* return TRUE if we did scroll */
624 return gtk_adjustment_get_value (hadj) != old_h_value || gtk_adjustment_get_value (vadj) != old_v_value;
625}
626
627static void
628pending_icon_to_reveal_destroy_callback (CajaIconCanvasItem *item,
629 CajaIconContainer *container)
630{
631 g_assert (CAJA_IS_ICON_CONTAINER (container));
632 g_assert (container->details->pending_icon_to_reveal != NULL);
633 g_assert (container->details->pending_icon_to_reveal->item == item);
634
635 container->details->pending_icon_to_reveal = NULL;
636}
637
638static CajaIcon*
639get_pending_icon_to_reveal (CajaIconContainer *container)
640{
641 return container->details->pending_icon_to_reveal;
642}
643
644static void
645set_pending_icon_to_reveal (CajaIconContainer *container, CajaIcon *icon)
646{
647 CajaIcon *old_icon;
648
649 old_icon = container->details->pending_icon_to_reveal;
650
651 if (icon == old_icon)
652 {
653 return;
654 }
655
656 if (old_icon != NULL)
657 {
658 g_signal_handlers_disconnect_by_func
659 (old_icon->item,
660 G_CALLBACK (pending_icon_to_reveal_destroy_callback),
661 container);
662 }
663
664 if (icon != NULL)
665 {
666 g_signal_connect (icon->item, "destroy",
667 G_CALLBACK (pending_icon_to_reveal_destroy_callback),
668 container);
669 }
670
671 container->details->pending_icon_to_reveal = icon;
672}
673
674static void
675item_get_canvas_bounds (EelCanvasItem *item,
676 EelIRect *bounds,
677 gboolean safety_pad)
678{
679 EelDRect world_rect;
680
681 eel_canvas_item_get_bounds (item,
682 &world_rect.x0,
683 &world_rect.y0,
684 &world_rect.x1,
685 &world_rect.y1);
686 eel_canvas_item_i2w (item->parent,
687 &world_rect.x0,
688 &world_rect.y0);
689 eel_canvas_item_i2w (item->parent,
690 &world_rect.x1,
691 &world_rect.y1);
692 if (safety_pad)
693 {
694 world_rect.x0 -= ICON_PAD_LEFT + ICON_PAD_RIGHT;
695 world_rect.x1 += ICON_PAD_LEFT + ICON_PAD_RIGHT;
696
697 world_rect.y0 -= ICON_PAD_TOP + ICON_PAD_BOTTOM;
698 world_rect.y1 += ICON_PAD_TOP + ICON_PAD_BOTTOM;
699 }
700
701 eel_canvas_w2c (item->canvas,
702 world_rect.x0,
703 world_rect.y0,
704 &bounds->x0,
705 &bounds->y0);
706 eel_canvas_w2c (item->canvas,
707 world_rect.x1,
708 world_rect.y1,
709 &bounds->x1,
710 &bounds->y1);
711}
712
713static void
714icon_get_row_and_column_bounds (CajaIconContainer *container,
715 CajaIcon *icon,
716 EelIRect *bounds,
717 gboolean safety_pad)
718{
719 GList *p;
720 EelIRect one_bounds;
721 CajaIcon *one_icon = NULL;
722
723 item_get_canvas_bounds (EEL_CANVAS_ITEM (icon->item), bounds, safety_pad);
724
725 for (p = container->details->icons; p != NULL; p = p->next) {
726 one_icon = p->data;
727
728 if (icon == one_icon) {
729 continue;
730 }
731
732 if (compare_icons_horizontal (container, icon, one_icon) == 0) {
733 item_get_canvas_bounds (EEL_CANVAS_ITEM (one_icon->item), &one_bounds, safety_pad);
734 bounds->x0 = MIN (bounds->x0, one_bounds.x0);
735 bounds->x1 = MAX (bounds->x1, one_bounds.x1);
736 }
737
738 if (compare_icons_vertical (container, icon, one_icon) == 0) {
739 item_get_canvas_bounds (EEL_CANVAS_ITEM (one_icon->item), &one_bounds, safety_pad);
740 bounds->y0 = MIN (bounds->y0, one_bounds.y0);
741 bounds->y1 = MAX (bounds->y1, one_bounds.y1);
742 }
743 }
744
745}
746
747static void
748reveal_icon (CajaIconContainer *container,
749 CajaIcon *icon)
750{
751 GtkAllocation allocation;
752 GtkAdjustment *hadj, *vadj;
753 EelIRect bounds;
754
755 if (!icon_is_positioned (icon)) {
756 set_pending_icon_to_reveal (container, icon);
757 return;
758 }
759
760 set_pending_icon_to_reveal (container, NULL);
761
762 gtk_widget_get_allocation (GTK_WIDGET (container), &allocation);
763
764 hadj = gtk_scrollable_get_hadjustment (GTK_SCROLLABLE (container));
765 vadj = gtk_scrollable_get_vadjustment (GTK_SCROLLABLE (container));
766
767 if (caja_icon_container_is_auto_layout (container)) {
768 /* ensure that we reveal the entire row/column */
769 icon_get_row_and_column_bounds (container, icon, &bounds, TRUE);
770 } else {
771 item_get_canvas_bounds (EEL_CANVAS_ITEM (icon->item), &bounds, TRUE);
772 }
773 if (bounds.y0 < gtk_adjustment_get_value (vadj)) {
774 gtk_adjustment_set_value (vadj, bounds.y0);
775 } else if (bounds.y1 > gtk_adjustment_get_value (vadj) + allocation.height) {
776 gtk_adjustment_set_value (vadj, bounds.y1 - allocation.height);
777 }
778
779 if (bounds.x0 < gtk_adjustment_get_value (hadj)) {
780 gtk_adjustment_set_value (hadj, bounds.x0);
781 } else if (bounds.x1 > gtk_adjustment_get_value (hadj) + allocation.width) {
782 if (bounds.x1 - allocation.width > bounds.x0) {
783 gtk_adjustment_set_value (hadj, bounds.x0);
784 } else {
785 gtk_adjustment_set_value (hadj, bounds.x1 - allocation.width);
786 }
787 }
788}
789
790static void
791process_pending_icon_to_reveal (CajaIconContainer *container)
792{
793 CajaIcon *pending_icon_to_reveal;
794
795 pending_icon_to_reveal = get_pending_icon_to_reveal (container);
796
797 if (pending_icon_to_reveal != NULL) {
798 reveal_icon (container, pending_icon_to_reveal);
799 }
800}
801
802static gboolean
803keyboard_icon_reveal_timeout_callback (gpointer data)
804{
805 CajaIconContainer *container;
806 CajaIcon *icon;
807
808 container = CAJA_ICON_CONTAINER (data);
809 icon = container->details->keyboard_icon_to_reveal;
810
811 g_assert (icon != NULL);
812
813 /* Only reveal the icon if it's still the keyboard focus or if
814 * it's still selected. Someone originally thought we should
815 * cancel this reveal if the user manages to sneak a direct
816 * scroll in before the timeout fires, but we later realized
817 * this wouldn't actually be an improvement
818 * (see bugzilla.gnome.org 40612).
819 */
820 if (icon == container->details->keyboard_focus
821 || icon->is_selected) {
822 reveal_icon (container, icon);
823 }
824 container->details->keyboard_icon_reveal_timer_id = 0;
825
826 return FALSE;
827}
828
829static void
830unschedule_keyboard_icon_reveal (CajaIconContainer *container)
831{
832 CajaIconContainerDetails *details;
833
834 details = container->details;
835
836 if (details->keyboard_icon_reveal_timer_id != 0) {
837 g_source_remove (details->keyboard_icon_reveal_timer_id);
838 }
839}
840
841static void
842schedule_keyboard_icon_reveal (CajaIconContainer *container,
843 CajaIcon *icon)
844{
845 CajaIconContainerDetails *details;
846
847 details = container->details;
848
849 unschedule_keyboard_icon_reveal (container);
850
851 details->keyboard_icon_to_reveal = icon;
852 details->keyboard_icon_reveal_timer_id
853 = g_timeout_add (KEYBOARD_ICON_REVEAL_TIMEOUT,
854 keyboard_icon_reveal_timeout_callback,
855 container);
856}
857
858static void
859clear_keyboard_focus (CajaIconContainer *container)
860{
861 if (container->details->keyboard_focus != NULL)
862 {
863 eel_canvas_item_set (EEL_CANVAS_ITEM (container->details->keyboard_focus->item),
864 "highlighted_as_keyboard_focus", 0,
865 NULL);
866 }
867
868 container->details->keyboard_focus = NULL;
869}
870
871static inline void
872emit_atk_focus_state_change (CajaIcon *icon, gboolean focused)
873{
874 AtkObject *atk_object = atk_gobject_accessible_for_object (G_OBJECT (icon->item));
875 atk_object_notify_state_change (atk_object, ATK_STATE_FOCUSED, focused);
876}
877
878/* Set @icon as the icon currently selected for keyboard operations. */
879static void
880set_keyboard_focus (CajaIconContainer *container,
881 CajaIcon *icon)
882{
883 g_assert (icon != NULL);
884
885 if (icon == container->details->keyboard_focus)
886 {
887 return;
888 }
889
890 clear_keyboard_focus (container);
891
892 container->details->keyboard_focus = icon;
893
894 eel_canvas_item_set (EEL_CANVAS_ITEM (container->details->keyboard_focus->item),
895 "highlighted_as_keyboard_focus", 1,
896 NULL);
897
898 emit_atk_focus_state_change (icon, TRUE);
899}

901static void
902set_keyboard_rubberband_start (CajaIconContainer *container,
903 CajaIcon *icon)
904{
905 container->details->keyboard_rubberband_start = icon;
906}

908static void
909clear_keyboard_rubberband_start (CajaIconContainer *container)
910{
911 container->details->keyboard_rubberband_start = NULL;
912}
913
914/* carbon-copy of eel_canvas_group_bounds(), but
915 * for CajaIconContainerItems it returns the
916 * bounds for the entire item.
917 */
918static void
919get_icon_bounds_for_canvas_bounds (EelCanvasGroup *group,
920 double *x1, double *y1,
921 double *x2, double *y2,
922 CajaIconCanvasItemBoundsUsage usage)
923{
924 EelCanvasItem *child;
925 GList *list;
926 double tx1, ty1, tx2, ty2;
927 double minx, miny, maxx, maxy;
928 int set;
929
930 /* Get the bounds of the first visible item */
931
932 child = NULL; /* Unnecessary but eliminates a warning. */
933
934 set = FALSE;
935
936 for (list = group->item_list; list; list = list->next)
937 {
938 child = list->data;
939
940 if (child->flags & EEL_CANVAS_ITEM_VISIBLE)
941 {
942 set = TRUE;
943 if (!CAJA_IS_ICON_CANVAS_ITEM (child) ||
944 usage == BOUNDS_USAGE_FOR_DISPLAY)
945 {
946 eel_canvas_item_get_bounds (child, &minx, &miny, &maxx, &maxy);
947 }
948 else if (usage == BOUNDS_USAGE_FOR_LAYOUT)
949 {
950 caja_icon_canvas_item_get_bounds_for_layout (CAJA_ICON_CANVAS_ITEM (child),
951 &minx, &miny, &maxx, &maxy);
952 }
953 else if (usage == BOUNDS_USAGE_FOR_ENTIRE_ITEM)
954 {
955 caja_icon_canvas_item_get_bounds_for_entire_item (CAJA_ICON_CANVAS_ITEM (child),
956 &minx, &miny, &maxx, &maxy);
957 }
958 else
959 {
960 g_assert_not_reached ();
961 }
962 break;
963 }
964 }
965
966 /* If there were no visible items, return an empty bounding box */
967
968 if (!set)
969 {
970 *x1 = *y1 = *x2 = *y2 = 0.0;
971 return;
972 }
973
974 /* Now we can grow the bounds using the rest of the items */
975
976 list = list->next;
977
978 for (; list; list = list->next)
979 {
980 child = list->data;
981
982 if (!(child->flags & EEL_CANVAS_ITEM_VISIBLE))
983 continue;
984
985 if (!CAJA_IS_ICON_CANVAS_ITEM (child) ||
986 usage == BOUNDS_USAGE_FOR_DISPLAY)
987 {
988 eel_canvas_item_get_bounds (child, &tx1, &ty1, &tx2, &ty2);
989 }
990 else if (usage == BOUNDS_USAGE_FOR_LAYOUT)
991 {
992 caja_icon_canvas_item_get_bounds_for_layout (CAJA_ICON_CANVAS_ITEM (child),
993 &tx1, &ty1, &tx2, &ty2);
994 }
995 else if (usage == BOUNDS_USAGE_FOR_ENTIRE_ITEM)
996 {
997 caja_icon_canvas_item_get_bounds_for_entire_item (CAJA_ICON_CANVAS_ITEM (child),
998 &tx1, &ty1, &tx2, &ty2);
999 }
1000 else
1001 {
1002 g_assert_not_reached ();
1003 }
1004
1005 if (tx1 < minx)
1006 minx = tx1;
1007
1008 if (ty1 < miny)
1009 miny = ty1;
1010
1011 if (tx2 > maxx)
1012 maxx = tx2;
1013
1014 if (ty2 > maxy)
1015 maxy = ty2;
1016 }
1017
1018 /* Make the bounds be relative to our parent's coordinate system */
1019
1020 if (EEL_CANVAS_ITEM (group)->parent)
1021 {
1022 minx += group->xpos;
1023 miny += group->ypos;
1024 maxx += group->xpos;
1025 maxy += group->ypos;
1026 }
1027
1028 if (x1 != NULL)
1029 {
1030 *x1 = minx;
1031 }
1032
1033 if (y1 != NULL)
1034 {
1035 *y1 = miny;
1036 }
1037
1038 if (x2 != NULL)
1039 {
1040 *x2 = maxx;
1041 }
1042
1043 if (y2 != NULL)
1044 {
1045 *y2 = maxy;
1046 }
1047}
1048
1049static void
1050get_all_icon_bounds (CajaIconContainer *container,
1051 double *x1, double *y1,
1052 double *x2, double *y2,
1053 CajaIconCanvasItemBoundsUsage usage)
1054{
1055 /* FIXME bugzilla.gnome.org 42477: Do we have to do something about the rubberband
1056 * here? Any other non-icon items?
1057 */
1058 get_icon_bounds_for_canvas_bounds (EEL_CANVAS_GROUP (EEL_CANVAS (container)->root),
1059 x1, y1, x2, y2, usage);
1060}
1061
1062/* Don't preserve visible white space the next time the scroll region
1063 * is recomputed when the container is not empty. */
1064void
1065caja_icon_container_reset_scroll_region (CajaIconContainer *container)
1066{
1067 container->details->reset_scroll_region_trigger = TRUE;
1068}
1069
1070/* Set a new scroll region without eliminating any of the currently-visible area. */
1071static void
1072canvas_set_scroll_region_include_visible_area (EelCanvas *canvas,
1073 double x1, double y1,
1074 double x2, double y2)
1075{
1076 double old_x1, old_y1, old_x2, old_y2;
1077 double old_scroll_x, old_scroll_y;
1078 double height, width;
1079 GtkAllocation allocation;
1080
1081 eel_canvas_get_scroll_region (canvas, &old_x1, &old_y1, &old_x2, &old_y2);
1082 gtk_widget_get_allocation (GTK_WIDGET (canvas), &allocation);
1083
1084 width = (allocation.width) / canvas->pixels_per_unit;
1085 height = (allocation.height) / canvas->pixels_per_unit;
1086
1087 old_scroll_x = gtk_adjustment_get_value (gtk_scrollable_get_hadjustment (GTK_SCROLLABLE (canvas)));
1088 old_scroll_y = gtk_adjustment_get_value (gtk_scrollable_get_vadjustment (GTK_SCROLLABLE (canvas)));
1089
1090 x1 = MIN (x1, old_x1 + old_scroll_x);
1091 y1 = MIN (y1, old_y1 + old_scroll_y);
1092 x2 = MAX (x2, old_x1 + old_scroll_x + width);
1093 y2 = MAX (y2, old_y1 + old_scroll_y + height);
1094
1095 eel_canvas_set_scroll_region
1096 (canvas, x1, y1, x2, y2);
1097}
1098
1099void
1100caja_icon_container_update_scroll_region (CajaIconContainer *container)
1101{
1102 double x1, y1, x2, y2;
1103 double pixels_per_unit;
1104 GtkAdjustment *hadj, *vadj;
1105 float step_increment;
1106 gboolean reset_scroll_region;
1107 GtkAllocation allocation;
1108
1109 pixels_per_unit = EEL_CANVAS (container)->pixels_per_unit;
1110
1111 if (caja_icon_container_get_is_fixed_size (container))
1112 {
1113 /* Set the scroll region to the size of the container allocation */
1114 gtk_widget_get_allocation (GTK_WIDGET (container), &allocation);
1115 eel_canvas_set_scroll_region
1116 (EEL_CANVAS (container),
1117 (double) - container->details->left_margin / pixels_per_unit,
1118 (double) - container->details->top_margin / pixels_per_unit,
1119 ((double) (allocation.width - 1)
1120 - container->details->left_margin
1121 - container->details->right_margin)
1122 / pixels_per_unit,
1123 ((double) (allocation.height - 1)
1124 - container->details->top_margin
1125 - container->details->bottom_margin)
1126 / pixels_per_unit);
1127 return;
1128 }
1129
1130 reset_scroll_region = container->details->reset_scroll_region_trigger
1131 || caja_icon_container_is_empty (container)
1132 || caja_icon_container_is_auto_layout (container);
1133
1134 /* The trigger is only cleared when container is non-empty, so
1135 * callers can reliably reset the scroll region when an item
1136 * is added even if extraneous relayouts are called when the
1137 * window is still empty.
1138 */
1139 if (!caja_icon_container_is_empty (container))
1140 {
1141 container->details->reset_scroll_region_trigger = FALSE;
1142 }
1143
1144 get_all_icon_bounds (container, &x1, &y1, &x2, &y2, BOUNDS_USAGE_FOR_ENTIRE_ITEM);
1145
1146 /* Add border at the "end"of the layout (i.e. after the icons), to
1147 * ensure we get some space when scrolled to the end.
1148 * For horizontal layouts, we add a bottom border.
1149 * Vertical layout is used by the compact view so the end
1150 * depends on the RTL setting.
1151 */
1152 if (caja_icon_container_is_layout_vertical (container))
1153 {
1154 if (caja_icon_container_is_layout_rtl (container))
1155 {
1156 x1 -= ICON_PAD_LEFT + CONTAINER_PAD_LEFT;
1157 }
1158 else
1159 {
1160 x2 += ICON_PAD_RIGHT + CONTAINER_PAD_RIGHT;
1161 }
1162 }
1163 else
1164 {
1165 y2 += ICON_PAD_BOTTOM + CONTAINER_PAD_BOTTOM;
1166 }
1167
1168 /* Auto-layout assumes a 0, 0 scroll origin and at least allocation->width.
1169 * Then we lay out to the right or to the left, so
1170 * x can be < 0 and > allocation */
1171 if (caja_icon_container_is_auto_layout (container))
1172 {
1173 gtk_widget_get_allocation (GTK_WIDGET (container), &allocation);
1174 x1 = MIN (x1, 0);
1175 x2 = MAX (x2, allocation.width / pixels_per_unit);
1176 y1 = 0;
1177 }
1178 else
1179 {
1180 /* Otherwise we add the padding that is at the start of the
1181 layout */
1182 if (caja_icon_container_is_layout_rtl (container))
1183 {
1184 x2 += ICON_PAD_RIGHT + CONTAINER_PAD_RIGHT;
1185 }
1186 else
1187 {
1188 x1 -= ICON_PAD_LEFT + CONTAINER_PAD_LEFT;
1189 }
1190 y1 -= ICON_PAD_TOP + CONTAINER_PAD_TOP;
1191 }
1192
1193 x2 -= 1;
1194 x2 = MAX(x1, x2);
1195
1196 y2 -= 1;
1197 y2 = MAX(y1, y2);
1198
1199 if (reset_scroll_region)
1200 {
1201 eel_canvas_set_scroll_region
1202 (EEL_CANVAS (container),
1203 x1, y1, x2, y2);
1204 }
1205 else
1206 {
1207 canvas_set_scroll_region_include_visible_area
1208 (EEL_CANVAS (container),
1209 x1, y1, x2, y2);
1210 }
1211
1212 hadj = gtk_scrollable_get_hadjustment (GTK_SCROLLABLE (container));
1213 vadj = gtk_scrollable_get_vadjustment (GTK_SCROLLABLE (container));
1214
1215 /* Scroll by 1/4 icon each time you click. */
1216 step_increment = caja_get_icon_size_for_zoom_level
1217 (container->details->zoom_level) / 4;
1218 if (gtk_adjustment_get_step_increment (hadj) != step_increment)
1219 {
1220 gtk_adjustment_set_step_increment (hadj, step_increment);
1221 }
1222 if (gtk_adjustment_get_step_increment (vadj) != step_increment)
1223 {
1224 gtk_adjustment_set_step_increment (vadj, step_increment);
1225 }
1226}
1227
1228static int
1229compare_icons (gconstpointer a, gconstpointer b, gpointer icon_container)
1230{
1231 CajaIconContainerClass *klass;
1232 const CajaIcon *icon_a, *icon_b;
1233
1234 icon_a = a;
1235 icon_b = b;
1236 klass = CAJA_ICON_CONTAINER_GET_CLASS (icon_container);
1237
1238 return klass->compare_icons (icon_container, icon_a->data, icon_b->data);
1239}
1240
1241static void
1242sort_icons (CajaIconContainer *container,
1243 GList **icons)
1244{
1245 CajaIconContainerClass *klass;
1246
1247 klass = CAJA_ICON_CONTAINER_GET_CLASS (container);
1248 g_assert (klass->compare_icons != NULL);
1249
1250 *icons = g_list_sort_with_data (*icons, compare_icons, container);
1251}
1252
1253static void
1254resort (CajaIconContainer *container)
1255{
1256 sort_icons (container, &container->details->icons);
1257}
1258
1259typedef struct
1260{
1261 double width;
1262 double height;
1263 double x_offset;
1264 double y_offset;
1265} IconPositions;
1266
1267static void
1268lay_down_one_line (CajaIconContainer *container,
1269 GList *line_start,
1270 GList *line_end,
1271 double y,
1272 double max_height,
1273 GArray *positions,
1274 gboolean whole_text)
1275{
1276 GList *p;
1277 double x, y_offset;
1278 IconPositions *position;
1279 int i;
1280 gboolean is_rtl;
1281 CajaIcon *icon = NULL;
1282
1283 is_rtl = caja_icon_container_is_layout_rtl (container);
1284
1285 /* Lay out the icons along the baseline. */
1286 x = ICON_PAD_LEFT;
1287 i = 0;
1288 for (p = line_start; p != line_end; p = p->next)
1289 {
1290 icon = p->data;
1291
1292 position = &g_array_index (positions, IconPositions, i++);
1293
1294 if (container->details->label_position == CAJA_ICON_LABEL_POSITION_BESIDE)
1295 {
1296 y_offset = (max_height - position->height) / 2;
1297 }
1298 else
1299 {
1300 y_offset = position->y_offset;
1301 }
1302
1303 icon_set_position
1304 (icon,
1305 is_rtl ? get_mirror_x_position (container, icon, x + position->x_offset) : x + position->x_offset,
1306 y + y_offset);
1307 caja_icon_canvas_item_set_entire_text (icon->item, whole_text);
1308
1309 icon->saved_ltr_x = is_rtl ? get_mirror_x_position (container, icon, icon->x) : icon->x;
1310
1311 x += position->width;
1312 }
1313}
1314
1315static void
1316lay_down_one_column (CajaIconContainer *container,
1317 GList *line_start,
1318 GList *line_end,
1319 double x,
1320 double y_start,
1321 double y_iter,
1322 GArray *positions)
1323{
1324 GList *p;
1325 double y;
1326 int i;
1327 gboolean is_rtl;
1328 IconPositions *position = NULL;
1329 CajaIcon *icon = NULL;
1330
1331 is_rtl = caja_icon_container_is_layout_rtl (container);
1332
1333 /* Lay out the icons along the baseline. */
1334 y = y_start;
1335 i = 0;
1336 for (p = line_start; p != line_end; p = p->next)
1337 {
1338 icon = p->data;
1339
1340 position = &g_array_index (positions, IconPositions, i++);
1341
1342 icon_set_position
1343 (icon,
1344 is_rtl ? get_mirror_x_position (container, icon, x + position->x_offset) : x + position->x_offset,
1345 y + position->y_offset);
1346
1347 icon->saved_ltr_x = is_rtl ? get_mirror_x_position (container, icon, icon->x) : icon->x;
1348
1349 y += y_iter;
1350 }
1351}
1352
1353static void
1354lay_down_icons_horizontal (CajaIconContainer *container,
1355 GList *icons,
1356 double start_y)
1357{
1358 GList *p, *line_start;
1359 CajaIcon *icon;
1360 double canvas_width, y;
1361 EelDRect bounds;
1362 EelDRect icon_bounds;
1363 EelDRect text_bounds;
1364 double max_height_above, max_height_below;
1365 double line_width;
1366 gboolean gridded_layout;
1367 double grid_width;
1368 double max_text_width, max_icon_width;
1369 int icon_width;
1370 int i;
1371 GtkAllocation allocation;
1372 GArray *positions;
1373 IconPositions *position = NULL;
1374
1375 g_assert (CAJA_IS_ICON_CONTAINER (container));
1376
1377 if (icons == NULL)
1378 {
1379 return;
1380 }
1381
1382 positions = g_array_new (FALSE, FALSE, sizeof (IconPositions));
1383 gtk_widget_get_allocation (GTK_WIDGET (container), &allocation);
1384
1385 /* Lay out icons a line at a time. */
1386 canvas_width = CANVAS_WIDTH(container, allocation);
1387 max_icon_width = max_text_width = 0.0;
1388
1389 if (container->details->label_position == CAJA_ICON_LABEL_POSITION_BESIDE)
1390 {
1391 /* Would it be worth caching these bounds for the next loop? */
1392 for (p = icons; p != NULL; p = p->next)
1393 {
1394 icon = p->data;
1395
1396 icon_bounds = caja_icon_canvas_item_get_icon_rectangle (icon->item);
1397 max_icon_width = MAX (max_icon_width, ceil (icon_bounds.x1 - icon_bounds.x0));
1398
1399 text_bounds = caja_icon_canvas_item_get_text_rectangle (icon->item, TRUE);
1400 max_text_width = MAX (max_text_width, ceil (text_bounds.x1 - text_bounds.x0));
1401 }
1402
1403 grid_width = max_icon_width + max_text_width + ICON_PAD_LEFT + ICON_PAD_RIGHT;
1404 }
1405 else
1406 {
1407 int num_columns;
1408
1409 num_columns = floor(canvas_width / STANDARD_ICON_GRID_WIDTH);
1410 num_columns = fmax(num_columns, 1);
1411 /* Minimum of one column */
1412 grid_width = canvas_width / num_columns - 1;
1413 /* -1 prevents jitter */
1414 }
1415
1416 gridded_layout = !caja_icon_container_is_tighter_layout (container);
1417
1418 line_width = container->details->label_position == CAJA_ICON_LABEL_POSITION_BESIDE ? ICON_PAD_LEFT : 0;
1419 line_start = icons;
1420 y = start_y + CONTAINER_PAD_TOP;
1421 i = 0;
1422
1423 max_height_above = 0;
1424 max_height_below = 0;
1425 for (p = icons; p != NULL; p = p->next)
1426 {
1427 double height_above, height_below;
1428
1429 icon = p->data;
1430
1431 /* Assume it's only one level hierarchy to avoid costly affine calculations */
1432 caja_icon_canvas_item_get_bounds_for_layout (icon->item,
1433 &bounds.x0, &bounds.y0,
1434 &bounds.x1, &bounds.y1);
1435
1436 icon_bounds = caja_icon_canvas_item_get_icon_rectangle (icon->item);
1437 text_bounds = caja_icon_canvas_item_get_text_rectangle (icon->item, TRUE);
1438
1439 if (gridded_layout)
1440 {
1441 icon_width = ceil ((bounds.x1 - bounds.x0)/grid_width) * grid_width;
1442
1443 }
1444 else
1445 {
1446 icon_width = (bounds.x1 - bounds.x0) + ICON_PAD_RIGHT + 8; /* 8 pixels extra for fancy selection box */
1447 }
1448
1449 /* Calculate size above/below baseline */
1450 height_above = icon_bounds.y1 - bounds.y0;
1451 height_below = bounds.y1 - icon_bounds.y1;
1452
1453 /* If this icon doesn't fit, it's time to lay out the line that's queued up. */
1454 if (line_start != p && line_width + icon_width >= canvas_width )
1455 {
1456 if (container->details->label_position == CAJA_ICON_LABEL_POSITION_BESIDE)
1457 {
1458 y += ICON_PAD_TOP;
1459 }
1460 else
1461 {
1462 /* Advance to the baseline. */
1463 y += ICON_PAD_TOP + max_height_above;
1464 }
1465
1466 lay_down_one_line (container, line_start, p, y, max_height_above, positions, FALSE);
1467
1468 if (container->details->label_position == CAJA_ICON_LABEL_POSITION_BESIDE)
1469 {
1470 y += max_height_above + max_height_below + ICON_PAD_BOTTOM;
1471 }
1472 else
1473 {
1474 /* Advance to next line. */
1475 y += max_height_below + ICON_PAD_BOTTOM;
1476 }
1477
1478 line_width = container->details->label_position == CAJA_ICON_LABEL_POSITION_BESIDE ? ICON_PAD_LEFT : 0;
1479 line_start = p;
1480 i = 0;
1481
1482 max_height_above = height_above;
1483 max_height_below = height_below;
1484 }
1485 else
1486 {
1487 if (height_above > max_height_above)
1488 {
1489 max_height_above = height_above;
1490 }
1491 if (height_below > max_height_below)
1492 {
1493 max_height_below = height_below;
1494 }
1495 }
1496
1497 g_array_set_size (positions, i + 1);
1498 position = &g_array_index (positions, IconPositions, i++);
1499 position->width = icon_width;
1500 position->height = icon_bounds.y1 - icon_bounds.y0;
1501
1502 if (container->details->label_position == CAJA_ICON_LABEL_POSITION_BESIDE)
1503 {
1504 if (gridded_layout)
1505 {
1506 position->x_offset = max_icon_width + ICON_PAD_LEFT + ICON_PAD_RIGHT - (icon_bounds.x1 - icon_bounds.x0);
1507 }
1508 else
1509 {
1510 position->x_offset = icon_width - ((icon_bounds.x1 - icon_bounds.x0) + (text_bounds.x1 - text_bounds.x0));
1511 }
1512 position->y_offset = 0;
1513 }
1514 else
1515 {
1516 position->x_offset = (icon_width - (icon_bounds.x1 - icon_bounds.x0)) / 2;
1517 position->y_offset = icon_bounds.y0 - icon_bounds.y1;
1518 }
1519
1520 /* Add this icon. */
1521 line_width += icon_width;
1522 }
1523
1524 /* Lay down that last line of icons. */
1525 if (line_start != NULL)
1526 {
1527 if (container->details->label_position == CAJA_ICON_LABEL_POSITION_BESIDE)
1528 {
1529 y += ICON_PAD_TOP;
1530 }
1531 else
1532 {
1533 /* Advance to the baseline. */
1534 y += ICON_PAD_TOP + max_height_above;
1535 }
1536
1537 lay_down_one_line (container, line_start, NULL, y, max_height_above, positions, TRUE);
1538
1539 /* Advance to next line. */
1540 y += max_height_below + ICON_PAD_BOTTOM;
1541 }
1542
1543 g_array_free (positions, TRUE);
1544}
1545
1546static void
1547get_max_icon_dimensions (GList *icon_start,
1548 GList *icon_end,
1549 double *max_icon_width,
1550 double *max_icon_height,
1551 double *max_text_width,
1552 double *max_text_height,
1553 double *max_bounds_height)
1554{
1555 EelDRect icon_bounds;
1556 EelDRect text_bounds;
1557 GList *p;
1558 double y1, y2;
1559 CajaIcon *icon = NULL;
1560
1561 *max_icon_width = *max_text_width = 0.0;
1562 *max_icon_height = *max_text_height = 0.0;
1563 *max_bounds_height = 0.0;
1564
1565 /* Would it be worth caching these bounds for the next loop? */
1566 for (p = icon_start; p != icon_end; p = p->next)
1567 {
1568 icon = p->data;
1569
1570 icon_bounds = caja_icon_canvas_item_get_icon_rectangle (icon->item);
1571 *max_icon_width = MAX (*max_icon_width, ceil (icon_bounds.x1 - icon_bounds.x0));
1572 *max_icon_height = MAX (*max_icon_height, ceil (icon_bounds.y1 - icon_bounds.y0));
1573
1574 text_bounds = caja_icon_canvas_item_get_text_rectangle (icon->item, TRUE);
1575 *max_text_width = MAX (*max_text_width, ceil (text_bounds.x1 - text_bounds.x0));
1576 *max_text_height = MAX (*max_text_height, ceil (text_bounds.y1 - text_bounds.y0));
1577
1578 caja_icon_canvas_item_get_bounds_for_layout (icon->item,
1579 NULL, &y1,
1580 NULL, &y2);
1581 *max_bounds_height = MAX (*max_bounds_height, y2 - y1);
1582 }
1583}
1584
1585/* column-wise layout. At the moment, this only works with label-beside-icon (used by "Compact View"). */
1586static void
1587lay_down_icons_vertical (CajaIconContainer *container,
1588 GList *icons,
1589 double start_y)
1590{
1591 GList *p, *line_start;
1592 double x, canvas_height;
1593 GArray *positions;
1594 IconPositions *position;
1595 EelDRect icon_bounds;
1596 EelDRect text_bounds;
1597 GtkAllocation allocation;
1598
1599 double line_height;
1600
1601 double max_height;
1602 double max_height_with_borders;
1603 double max_width;
1604 double max_width_in_column;
1605
1606 double max_bounds_height;
1607 double max_bounds_height_with_borders;
1608
1609 double max_text_width, max_icon_width;
1610 double max_text_height, max_icon_height;
1611 int i;
1612
1613 CajaIcon *icon = NULL;
1614
1615 g_assert (CAJA_IS_ICON_CONTAINER (container));
1616 g_assert (container->details->label_position == CAJA_ICON_LABEL_POSITION_BESIDE);
1617
1618 if (icons == NULL)
1619 {
1620 return;
1621 }
1622
1623 positions = g_array_new (FALSE, FALSE, sizeof (IconPositions));
1624 gtk_widget_get_allocation (GTK_WIDGET (container), &allocation);
1625
1626 /* Lay out icons a column at a time. */
1627 canvas_height = CANVAS_HEIGHT(container, allocation);
1628
1629 max_icon_width = max_text_width = 0.0;
1630 max_icon_height = max_text_height = 0.0;
1631 max_bounds_height = 0.0;
1632
1633 get_max_icon_dimensions (icons, NULL,
1634 &max_icon_width, &max_icon_height,
1635 &max_text_width, &max_text_height,
1636 &max_bounds_height);
1637
1638 max_width = max_icon_width + max_text_width;
1639 max_height = MAX (max_icon_height, max_text_height);
1640 max_height_with_borders = ICON_PAD_TOP + max_height;
1641
1642 max_bounds_height_with_borders = ICON_PAD_TOP + max_bounds_height;
1643
1644 line_height = ICON_PAD_TOP;
1645 line_start = icons;
1646 x = 0;
1647 i = 0;
1648
1649 max_width_in_column = 0.0;
1650
1651 for (p = icons; p != NULL; p = p->next)
1652 {
1653 int height;
1654
1655 icon = p->data;
1656
1657 /* If this icon doesn't fit, it's time to lay out the column that's queued up. */
1658
1659 /* We use the bounds height here, since for wrapping we also want to consider
1660 * overlapping emblems at the bottom. We may wrap a little bit too early since
1661 * the icon with the max. bounds height may actually not be in the last row, but
1662 * it is better than visual glitches
1663 */
1664 if (line_start != p && line_height + (max_bounds_height_with_borders-1) >= canvas_height )
1665 {
1666 x += ICON_PAD_LEFT;
1667
1668 /* correctly set (per-column) width */
1669 if (!container->details->all_columns_same_width)
1670 {
1671 for (i = 0; i < (int) positions->len; i++)
1672 {
1673 position = &g_array_index (positions, IconPositions, i);
1674 position->width = max_width_in_column;
1675 }
1676 }
1677
1678 lay_down_one_column (container, line_start, p, x, CONTAINER_PAD_TOP, max_height_with_borders, positions);
1679
1680 /* Advance to next column. */
1681 if (container->details->all_columns_same_width)
1682 {
1683 x += max_width + ICON_PAD_RIGHT;
1684 }
1685 else
1686 {
1687 x += max_width_in_column + ICON_PAD_RIGHT;
1688 }
1689
1690 line_height = ICON_PAD_TOP;
1691 line_start = p;
1692 i = 0;
1693
1694 max_width_in_column = 0;
1695 }
1696
1697 icon_bounds = caja_icon_canvas_item_get_icon_rectangle (icon->item);
1698 text_bounds = caja_icon_canvas_item_get_text_rectangle (icon->item, TRUE);
1699
1700 max_width_in_column = MAX (max_width_in_column,
1701 ceil (icon_bounds.x1 - icon_bounds.x0) +
1702 ceil (text_bounds.x1 - text_bounds.x0));
1703
1704 g_array_set_size (positions, i + 1);
1705 position = &g_array_index (positions, IconPositions, i++);
1706 if (container->details->all_columns_same_width)
1707 {
1708 position->width = max_width;
1709 }
1710 position->height = max_height;
1711 position->y_offset = ICON_PAD_TOP;
1712 position->x_offset = ICON_PAD_LEFT;
1713
1714 position->x_offset += max_icon_width - ceil (icon_bounds.x1 - icon_bounds.x0);
1715
1716 height = MAX (ceil (icon_bounds.y1 - icon_bounds.y0), ceil(text_bounds.y1 - text_bounds.y0));
1717 position->y_offset += (max_height - height) / 2;
1718
1719 /* Add this icon. */
1720 line_height += max_height_with_borders;
1721 }
1722
1723 /* Lay down that last column of icons. */
1724 if (line_start != NULL)
1725 {
1726 x += ICON_PAD_LEFT;
1727 lay_down_one_column (container, line_start, NULL, x, CONTAINER_PAD_TOP, max_height_with_borders, positions);
1728 }
1729
1730 g_array_free (positions, TRUE);
1731}
1732
1733static void
1734snap_position (CajaIconContainer *container,
1735 CajaIcon *icon,
1736 int *x, int *y)
1737{
1738 int center_x;
1739 int baseline_y;
1740 int icon_width;
1741 int icon_height;
1742 int total_width;
1743 int total_height;
1744 EelDRect icon_position;
1745 GtkAllocation allocation;
1746
1747 icon_position = caja_icon_canvas_item_get_icon_rectangle (icon->item);
1748 icon_width = icon_position.x1 - icon_position.x0;
1749 icon_height = icon_position.y1 - icon_position.y0;
1750
1751 gtk_widget_get_allocation (GTK_WIDGET (container), &allocation);
1752 total_width = CANVAS_WIDTH (container, allocation);
1753 total_height = CANVAS_HEIGHT (container, allocation);
1754
1755 if (caja_icon_container_is_layout_rtl (container))
1756 *x = get_mirror_x_position (container, icon, *x);
1757
1758 if (*x + icon_width / 2 < DESKTOP_PAD_HORIZONTAL + SNAP_SIZE_X)
1759 {
1760 *x = DESKTOP_PAD_HORIZONTAL + SNAP_SIZE_X - icon_width / 2;
1761 }
1762
1763 if (*x + icon_width / 2 > total_width - (DESKTOP_PAD_HORIZONTAL + SNAP_SIZE_X))
1764 {
1765 *x = total_width - (DESKTOP_PAD_HORIZONTAL + SNAP_SIZE_X + (icon_width / 2));
1766 }
1767
1768 if (*y + icon_height < DESKTOP_PAD_VERTICAL + SNAP_SIZE_Y)
1769 {
1770 *y = DESKTOP_PAD_VERTICAL + SNAP_SIZE_Y - icon_height;
1771 }
1772
1773 if (*y + icon_height > total_height - (DESKTOP_PAD_VERTICAL + SNAP_SIZE_Y))
1774 {
1775 *y = total_height - (DESKTOP_PAD_VERTICAL + SNAP_SIZE_Y + (icon_height / 2));
1776 }
1777
1778 center_x = *x + icon_width / 2;
1779 *x = SNAP_NEAREST_HORIZONTAL (center_x) - (icon_width / 2);
1780 if (caja_icon_container_is_layout_rtl (container))
1781 {
1782 *x = get_mirror_x_position (container, icon, *x);
1783 }
1784
1785 /* Find the grid position vertically and place on the proper baseline */
1786 baseline_y = *y + icon_height;
1787 baseline_y = SNAP_NEAREST_VERTICAL (baseline_y);
1788 *y = baseline_y - icon_height;
1789}
1790
1791static int
1792compare_icons_by_position (gconstpointer a, gconstpointer b)
1793{
1794 CajaIcon *icon_a, *icon_b;
1795 int x1, y1, x2, y2;
1796 int center_a;
1797 int center_b;
1798
1799 icon_a = (CajaIcon*)a;
1800 icon_b = (CajaIcon*)b;
1801
1802 icon_get_bounding_box (icon_a, &x1, &y1, &x2, &y2,
1803 BOUNDS_USAGE_FOR_DISPLAY);
1804 center_a = x1 + (x2 - x1) / 2;
1805 icon_get_bounding_box (icon_b, &x1, &y1, &x2, &y2,
1806 BOUNDS_USAGE_FOR_DISPLAY);
1807 center_b = x1 + (x2 - x1) / 2;
1808
1809 return center_a == center_b ?
1810 icon_a->y - icon_b->y :
1811 center_a - center_b;
1812}
1813
1814static PlacementGrid *
1815placement_grid_new (CajaIconContainer *container, gboolean tight)
1816{
1817 PlacementGrid *grid;
1818 int width, height;
1819 int num_columns;
1820 int num_rows;
1821 int i;
1822 GtkAllocation allocation;
1823
1824 /* Get container dimensions */
1825 gtk_widget_get_allocation (GTK_WIDGET (container), &allocation);
1826 width = CANVAS_WIDTH(container, allocation);
1827 height = CANVAS_HEIGHT(container, allocation);
1828
1829 num_columns = width / SNAP_SIZE_X;
1830 num_rows = height / SNAP_SIZE_Y;
1831
1832 if (num_columns == 0 || num_rows == 0)
1833 {
1834 return NULL;
1835 }
1836
1837 grid = g_new0 (PlacementGrid, 1);
1838 grid->tight = tight;
1839 grid->num_columns = num_columns;
1840 grid->num_rows = num_rows;
1841
1842 grid->grid_memory = g_new0 (int, (num_rows * num_columns));
1843 grid->icon_grid = g_new0 (int *, num_columns);
1844
1845 for (i = 0; i < num_columns; i++)
1846 {
1847 grid->icon_grid[i] = grid->grid_memory + (i * num_rows);
1848 }
1849
1850 return grid;
1851}
1852
1853static void
1854placement_grid_free (PlacementGrid *grid)
1855{
1856 g_free (grid->icon_grid);
1857 g_free (grid->grid_memory);
1858 g_free (grid);
1859}
1860
1861static gboolean
1862placement_grid_position_is_free (PlacementGrid *grid, EelIRect pos)
1863{
1864 int x, y;
1865
1866 g_assert (pos.x0 >= 0 && pos.x0 < grid->num_columns);
1867 g_assert (pos.y0 >= 0 && pos.y0 < grid->num_rows);
1868 g_assert (pos.x1 >= 0 && pos.x1 < grid->num_columns);
1869 g_assert (pos.y1 >= 0 && pos.y1 < grid->num_rows);
1870
1871 for (x = pos.x0; x <= pos.x1; x++)
1872 {
1873 for (y = pos.y0; y <= pos.y1; y++)
1874 {
1875 if (grid->icon_grid[x][y] != 0)
1876 {
1877 return FALSE;
1878 }
1879 }
1880 }
1881
1882 return TRUE;
1883}
1884
1885static void
1886placement_grid_mark (PlacementGrid *grid, EelIRect pos)
1887{
1888 int x, y;
1889
1890 g_assert (pos.x0 >= 0 && pos.x0 < grid->num_columns);
1891 g_assert (pos.y0 >= 0 && pos.y0 < grid->num_rows);
1892 g_assert (pos.x1 >= 0 && pos.x1 < grid->num_columns);
1893 g_assert (pos.y1 >= 0 && pos.y1 < grid->num_rows);
1894
1895 for (x = pos.x0; x <= pos.x1; x++)
1896 {
1897 for (y = pos.y0; y <= pos.y1; y++)
1898 {
1899 grid->icon_grid[x][y] = 1;
1900 }
1901 }
1902}
1903
1904static void
1905canvas_position_to_grid_position (PlacementGrid *grid,
1906 EelIRect canvas_position,
1907 EelIRect *grid_position)
1908{
1909 /* The first causes minimal moving around during a snap, but
1910 * can end up with partially overlapping icons. The second one won't
1911 * allow any overlapping, but can cause more movement to happen
1912 * during a snap. */
1913 if (grid->tight)
1914 {
1915 grid_position->x0 = ceil ((double)(canvas_position.x0 - DESKTOP_PAD_HORIZONTAL) / SNAP_SIZE_X);
1916 grid_position->y0 = ceil ((double)(canvas_position.y0 - DESKTOP_PAD_VERTICAL) / SNAP_SIZE_Y);
1917 grid_position->x1 = floor ((double)(canvas_position.x1 - DESKTOP_PAD_HORIZONTAL) / SNAP_SIZE_X);
1918 grid_position->y1 = floor ((double)(canvas_position.y1 - DESKTOP_PAD_VERTICAL) / SNAP_SIZE_Y);
1919 }
1920 else
1921 {
1922 grid_position->x0 = floor ((double)(canvas_position.x0 - DESKTOP_PAD_HORIZONTAL) / SNAP_SIZE_X);
1923 grid_position->y0 = floor ((double)(canvas_position.y0 - DESKTOP_PAD_VERTICAL) / SNAP_SIZE_Y);
1924 grid_position->x1 = floor ((double)(canvas_position.x1 - DESKTOP_PAD_HORIZONTAL) / SNAP_SIZE_X);
1925 grid_position->y1 = floor ((double)(canvas_position.y1 - DESKTOP_PAD_VERTICAL) / SNAP_SIZE_Y);
1926 }
1927
1928 grid_position->x0 = CLAMP (grid_position->x0, 0, grid->num_columns - 1);
1929 grid_position->y0 = CLAMP (grid_position->y0, 0, grid->num_rows - 1);
1930 grid_position->x1 = CLAMP (grid_position->x1, grid_position->x0, grid->num_columns - 1);
1931 grid_position->y1 = CLAMP (grid_position->y1, grid_position->y0, grid->num_rows - 1);
1932}
1933
1934static void
1935placement_grid_mark_icon (PlacementGrid *grid, CajaIcon *icon)
1936{
1937 EelIRect icon_pos;
1938 EelIRect grid_pos;
1939
1940 icon_get_bounding_box (icon,
1941 &icon_pos.x0, &icon_pos.y0,
1942 &icon_pos.x1, &icon_pos.y1,
1943 BOUNDS_USAGE_FOR_LAYOUT);
1944 canvas_position_to_grid_position (grid,
1945 icon_pos,
1946 &grid_pos);
1947 placement_grid_mark (grid, grid_pos);
1948}
1949
1950static void
1951find_empty_location (CajaIconContainer *container,
1952 PlacementGrid *grid,
1953 CajaIcon *icon,
1954 int start_x,
1955 int start_y,
1956 int *x,
1957 int *y)
1958{
1959 double icon_width, icon_height;
1960 int canvas_width;
1961 int canvas_height;
1962 int height_for_bound_check;
1963 EelIRect icon_position;
1964 EelDRect pixbuf_rect;
1965 gboolean collision;
1966 GtkAllocation allocation;
1967
1968 /* Get container dimensions */
1969 gtk_widget_get_allocation (GTK_WIDGET (container), &allocation);
1970 canvas_width = CANVAS_WIDTH(container, allocation);
1971 canvas_height = CANVAS_HEIGHT(container, allocation);
1972
1973 icon_get_bounding_box (icon,
1974 &icon_position.x0, &icon_position.y0,
1975 &icon_position.x1, &icon_position.y1,
1976 BOUNDS_USAGE_FOR_LAYOUT);
1977 icon_width = icon_position.x1 - icon_position.x0;
1978 icon_height = icon_position.y1 - icon_position.y0;
1979
1980 icon_get_bounding_box (icon,
1981 NULL, &icon_position.y0,
1982 NULL, &icon_position.y1,
1983 BOUNDS_USAGE_FOR_ENTIRE_ITEM);
1984 height_for_bound_check = icon_position.y1 - icon_position.y0;
1985
1986 pixbuf_rect = caja_icon_canvas_item_get_icon_rectangle (icon->item);
1987
1988 /* Start the icon on a grid location */
1989 snap_position (container, icon, &start_x, &start_y);
1990
1991 icon_position.x0 = start_x;
1992 icon_position.y0 = start_y;
1993 icon_position.x1 = icon_position.x0 + icon_width;
1994 icon_position.y1 = icon_position.y0 + icon_height;
1995
1996 do
1997 {
1998 EelIRect grid_position;
1999 gboolean need_new_column;
2000
2001 collision = FALSE;
2002
2003 canvas_position_to_grid_position (grid,
2004 icon_position,
2005 &grid_position);
2006
2007 need_new_column = icon_position.y0 + height_for_bound_check + DESKTOP_PAD_VERTICAL > canvas_height;
2008
2009 if (need_new_column ||
2010 !placement_grid_position_is_free (grid, grid_position))
2011 {
2012 icon_position.y0 += SNAP_SIZE_Y;
2013 icon_position.y1 = icon_position.y0 + icon_height;
2014
2015 if (need_new_column)
2016 {
2017 /* Move to the next column */
2018 icon_position.y0 = DESKTOP_PAD_VERTICAL + SNAP_SIZE_Y - (pixbuf_rect.y1 - pixbuf_rect.y0);
2019 while (icon_position.y0 < DESKTOP_PAD_VERTICAL)
2020 {
2021 icon_position.y0 += SNAP_SIZE_Y;
2022 }
2023 icon_position.y1 = icon_position.y0 + icon_height;
2024
2025 icon_position.x0 += SNAP_SIZE_X;
2026 icon_position.x1 = icon_position.x0 + icon_width;
2027 }
2028
2029 collision = TRUE;
2030 }
2031 }
2032 while (collision && (icon_position.x1 < canvas_width));
2033
2034 *x = icon_position.x0;
2035 *y = icon_position.y0;
2036}
2037
2038static void
2039align_icons (CajaIconContainer *container)
2040{
2041 GList *unplaced_icons;
2042 GList *l;
2043 PlacementGrid *grid;
2044
2045 unplaced_icons = g_list_copy (container->details->icons);
2046
2047 unplaced_icons = g_list_sort (unplaced_icons,
2048 compare_icons_by_position);
2049
2050 if (caja_icon_container_is_layout_rtl (container))
2051 {
2052 unplaced_icons = g_list_reverse (unplaced_icons);
2053 }
2054
2055 grid = placement_grid_new (container, TRUE);
2056
2057 if (!grid)
2058 {
2059 g_list_free (unplaced_icons);
2060 return;
2061 }
2062
2063 for (l = unplaced_icons; l != NULL; l = l->next)
2064 {
2065 CajaIcon *icon;
2066 int x, y;
2067
2068 icon = l->data;
2069 x = icon->saved_ltr_x;
2070 y = icon->y;
2071 find_empty_location (container, grid,
2072 icon, x, y, &x, &y);
2073
2074 icon_set_position (icon, x, y);
2075 icon->saved_ltr_x = icon->x;
2076 placement_grid_mark_icon (grid, icon);
2077 }
2078
2079 g_list_free (unplaced_icons);
2080
2081 placement_grid_free (grid);
2082
2083 if (caja_icon_container_is_layout_rtl (container))
2084 {
2085 caja_icon_container_set_rtl_positions (container);
2086 }
2087}
2088
2089static double
2090get_mirror_x_position (CajaIconContainer *container, CajaIcon *icon, double x)
2091{
2092 EelDRect icon_bounds;
2093 GtkAllocation allocation;
2094
2095 gtk_widget_get_allocation (GTK_WIDGET (container), &allocation);
2096 icon_bounds = caja_icon_canvas_item_get_icon_rectangle (icon->item);
2097
2098 return CANVAS_WIDTH(container, allocation) - x - (icon_bounds.x1 - icon_bounds.x0);
2099}
2100
2101static void
2102caja_icon_container_set_rtl_positions (CajaIconContainer *container)
2103{
2104 GList *l;
2105 CajaIcon *icon = NULL;
2106
2107 if (!container->details->icons)
2108 {
2109 return;
2110 }
2111
2112 for (l = container->details->icons; l != NULL; l = l->next)
2113 {
2114 double x;
2115
2116 icon = l->data;
2117 x = get_mirror_x_position (container, icon, icon->saved_ltr_x);
2118 icon_set_position (icon, x, icon->y);
2119 }
2120}
2121
2122static void
2123lay_down_icons_vertical_desktop (CajaIconContainer *container, GList *icons)
2124{
2125 GList *p, *placed_icons, *unplaced_icons;
2126 int total, new_length, placed;
2127 CajaIcon *icon;
2128 int height;
2129 int x, y, x1, x2, y1, y2;
2130 EelDRect icon_rect;
2131 GtkAllocation allocation;
2132
2133 /* Get container dimensions */
2134 gtk_widget_get_allocation (GTK_WIDGET (container), &allocation);
2135 height = CANVAS_HEIGHT(container, allocation);
2136
2137 /* Determine which icons have and have not been placed */
2138 placed_icons = NULL;
2139 unplaced_icons = NULL;
2140
2141 total = g_list_length (container->details->icons);
2142 new_length = g_list_length (icons);
2143 placed = total - new_length;
2144 if (placed > 0)
2145 {
2146 PlacementGrid *grid;
2147 /* Add only placed icons in list */
2148 for (p = container->details->icons; p != NULL; p = p->next)
2149 {
2150 icon = p->data;
2151 if (icon_is_positioned (icon))
2152 {
2153 icon_set_position(icon, icon->saved_ltr_x, icon->y);
2154 placed_icons = g_list_prepend (placed_icons, icon);
2155 }
2156 else
2157 {
2158 icon->x = 0;
2159 icon->y = 0;
2160 unplaced_icons = g_list_prepend (unplaced_icons, icon);
2161 }
2162 }
2163 placed_icons = g_list_reverse (placed_icons);
2164 unplaced_icons = g_list_reverse (unplaced_icons);
2165
2166 grid = placement_grid_new (container, FALSE);
2167
2168 if (grid)
2169 {
2170 for (p = placed_icons; p != NULL; p = p->next)
2171 {
2172 placement_grid_mark_icon
2173 (grid, (CajaIcon*)p->data);
2174 }
2175
2176 /* Place unplaced icons in the best locations */
2177 for (p = unplaced_icons; p != NULL; p = p->next)
2178 {
2179 icon = p->data;
2180
2181 icon_rect = caja_icon_canvas_item_get_icon_rectangle (icon->item);
2182
2183 /* Start the icon in the first column */
2184 x = DESKTOP_PAD_HORIZONTAL + (SNAP_SIZE_X / 2) - ((icon_rect.x1 - icon_rect.x0) / 2);
2185 y = DESKTOP_PAD_VERTICAL + SNAP_SIZE_Y - (icon_rect.y1 - icon_rect.y0);
2186
2187 find_empty_location (container,
2188 grid,
2189 icon,
2190 x, y,
2191 &x, &y);
2192
2193 icon_set_position (icon, x, y);
2194 icon->saved_ltr_x = x;
2195 placement_grid_mark_icon (grid, icon);
2196 }
2197
2198 placement_grid_free (grid);
2199 }
2200
2201 g_list_free (placed_icons);
2202 g_list_free (unplaced_icons);
2203 }
2204 else
2205 {
2206 /* There are no placed icons. Just lay them down using our rules */
2207 x = DESKTOP_PAD_HORIZONTAL;
2208
2209 while (icons != NULL)
2210 {
2211 int max_width, column_width, icon_height;
2212 int center_x;
2213 int baseline;
2214 int icon_height_for_bound_check;
2215 gboolean should_snap;
2216
2217 should_snap = !(container->details->tighter_layout && !container->details->keep_aligned);
2218
2219 y = DESKTOP_PAD_VERTICAL;
2220
2221 max_width = 0;
2222
2223 /* Calculate max width for column */
2224 for (p = icons; p != NULL; p = p->next)
2225 {
2226 int icon_width;
2227
2228 icon = p->data;
2229
2230 icon_get_bounding_box (icon, &x1, &y1, &x2, &y2,
2231 BOUNDS_USAGE_FOR_LAYOUT);
2232 icon_width = x2 - x1;
2233 icon_height = y2 - y1;
2234
2235 icon_get_bounding_box (icon, NULL, &y1, NULL, &y2,
2236 BOUNDS_USAGE_FOR_ENTIRE_ITEM);
2237 icon_height_for_bound_check = y2 - y1;
2238
2239 if (should_snap)
2240 {
2241 /* Snap the baseline to a grid position */
2242 icon_rect = caja_icon_canvas_item_get_icon_rectangle (icon->item);
2243 baseline = y + (icon_rect.y1 - icon_rect.y0);
2244 baseline = SNAP_CEIL_VERTICAL (baseline);
2245 y = baseline - (icon_rect.y1 - icon_rect.y0);
2246 }
2247
2248 /* Check and see if we need to move to a new column */
2249 if (y != DESKTOP_PAD_VERTICAL && y + icon_height_for_bound_check > height)
2250 {
2251 break;
2252 }
2253
2254 if (max_width < icon_width)
2255 {
2256 max_width = icon_width;
2257 }
2258
2259 y += icon_height + DESKTOP_PAD_VERTICAL;
2260 }
2261
2262 y = DESKTOP_PAD_VERTICAL;
2263
2264 center_x = x + max_width / 2;
2265 column_width = max_width;
2266 if (should_snap)
2267 {
2268 /* Find the grid column to center on */
2269 center_x = SNAP_CEIL_HORIZONTAL (center_x);
2270 column_width = (center_x - x) + (max_width / 2);
2271 }
2272
2273 /* Lay out column */
2274 for (p = icons; p != NULL; p = p->next)
2275 {
2276 icon = p->data;
2277 icon_get_bounding_box (icon, &x1, &y1, &x2, &y2,
2278 BOUNDS_USAGE_FOR_LAYOUT);
2279 icon_height = y2 - y1;
2280
2281 icon_get_bounding_box (icon, NULL, &y1, NULL, &y2,
2282 BOUNDS_USAGE_FOR_ENTIRE_ITEM);
2283 icon_height_for_bound_check = y2 - y1;
2284
2285 icon_rect = caja_icon_canvas_item_get_icon_rectangle (icon->item);
2286
2287 if (should_snap)
2288 {
2289 baseline = y + (icon_rect.y1 - icon_rect.y0);
2290 baseline = SNAP_CEIL_VERTICAL (baseline);
2291 y = baseline - (icon_rect.y1 - icon_rect.y0);
2292 }
2293
2294 /* Check and see if we need to move to a new column */
2295 if (y != DESKTOP_PAD_VERTICAL && y > height - icon_height_for_bound_check &&
2296 /* Make sure we lay out at least one icon per column, to make progress */
2297 p != icons)
2298 {
2299 x += column_width + DESKTOP_PAD_HORIZONTAL;
2300 break;
2301 }
2302
2303 icon_set_position (icon,
2304 center_x - (icon_rect.x1 - icon_rect.x0) / 2,
2305 y);
2306
2307 icon->saved_ltr_x = icon->x;
2308 y += icon_height + DESKTOP_PAD_VERTICAL;
2309 }
2310 icons = p;
2311 }
2312 }
2313
2314 /* These modes are special. We freeze all of our positions
2315 * after we do the layout.
2316 */
2317 /* FIXME bugzilla.gnome.org 42478:
2318 * This should not be tied to the direction of layout.
2319 * It should be a separate switch.
2320 */
2321 caja_icon_container_freeze_icon_positions (container);
2322}
2323
2324static void
2325lay_down_icons (CajaIconContainer *container, GList *icons, double start_y)
2326{
2327 switch (container->details->layout_mode)
2328 {
2329 case CAJA_ICON_LAYOUT_L_R_T_B:
2330 case CAJA_ICON_LAYOUT_R_L_T_B:
2331 lay_down_icons_horizontal (container, icons, start_y);
2332 break;
2333
2334 case CAJA_ICON_LAYOUT_T_B_L_R:
2335 case CAJA_ICON_LAYOUT_T_B_R_L:
2336 if (caja_icon_container_get_is_desktop (container))
2337 {
2338 lay_down_icons_vertical_desktop (container, icons);
2339 }
2340 else
2341 {
2342 lay_down_icons_vertical (container, icons, start_y);
2343 }
2344 break;
2345
2346 default:
2347 g_assert_not_reached ();
2348 }
2349}
2350
2351static void
2352redo_layout_internal (CajaIconContainer *container)
2353{
2354 finish_adding_new_icons (container);
2355
2356 /* Don't do any re-laying-out during stretching. Later we
2357 * might add smart logic that does this and leaves room for
2358 * the stretched icon, but if we do it we want it to be fast
2359 * and only re-lay-out when it's really needed.
2360 */
2361 if (container->details->auto_layout
2362 && container->details->drag_state != DRAG_STATE_STRETCH)
2363 {
2364 resort (container);
2365 lay_down_icons (container, container->details->icons, 0);
2366 }
2367
2368 if (caja_icon_container_is_layout_rtl (container))
2369 {
2370 caja_icon_container_set_rtl_positions (container);
2371 }
2372
2373 caja_icon_container_update_scroll_region (container);
2374
2375 process_pending_icon_to_reveal (container);
2376 process_pending_icon_to_rename (container);
2377 caja_icon_container_update_visible_icons (container);
2378}
2379
2380static gboolean
2381redo_layout_callback (gpointer callback_data)
2382{
2383 CajaIconContainer *container;
2384
2385 container = CAJA_ICON_CONTAINER (callback_data);
2386 redo_layout_internal (container);
2387 container->details->idle_id = 0;
2388
2389 return FALSE;
2390}
2391
2392static void
2393unschedule_redo_layout (CajaIconContainer *container)
2394{
2395 if (container->details->idle_id != 0)
2396 {
2397 g_source_remove (container->details->idle_id);
2398 container->details->idle_id = 0;
2399 }
2400}
2401
2402static void
2403schedule_redo_layout (CajaIconContainer *container)
2404{
2405 if (container->details->idle_id == 0
2406 && container->details->has_been_allocated)
2407 {
2408 container->details->idle_id = g_idle_add
2409 (redo_layout_callback, container);
2410 }
2411}
2412
2413static void
2414redo_layout (CajaIconContainer *container)
2415{
2416 unschedule_redo_layout (container);
2417 redo_layout_internal (container);
2418}
2419
2420static void
2421reload_icon_positions (CajaIconContainer *container,
2422 gboolean layout_changed)
2423{
2424 GList *p, *no_position_icons;
2425 gboolean have_stored_position;
2426 CajaIconPosition position;
2427 EelDRect bounds;
2428 double bottom;
2429 EelCanvasItem *item;
2430 CajaIcon *icon = NULL;
2431
2432 g_assert (!container->details->auto_layout);
2433
2434 resort (container);
2435
2436 no_position_icons = NULL;
2437
2438 /* Place all the icons with positions. */
2439 bottom = 0;
2440 for (p = container->details->icons; p != NULL; p = p->next)
2441 {
2442 icon = p->data;
2443
2444 have_stored_position = FALSE;
2445 g_signal_emit (container,
2446 signals[GET_STORED_ICON_POSITION], 0,
2447 icon->data,
2448 &position,
2449 &have_stored_position);
2450 if (have_stored_position)
2451 {
2452 icon_set_position_full (icon, position.x, position.y,
2453 /* if only layout changed, don't bother
2454 * updating already valid info. If however
2455 * e.g. zoom changed, x and y might now be
2456 * overflowing and need recomputing */
2457 !layout_changed);
2458 item = EEL_CANVAS_ITEM (icon->item);
2459 caja_icon_canvas_item_get_bounds_for_layout (icon->item,
2460 &bounds.x0,
2461 &bounds.y0,
2462 &bounds.x1,
2463 &bounds.y1);
2464 eel_canvas_item_i2w (item->parent,
2465 &bounds.x0,
2466 &bounds.y0);
2467 eel_canvas_item_i2w (item->parent,
2468 &bounds.x1,
2469 &bounds.y1);
2470 if (bounds.y1 > bottom)
2471 {
2472 bottom = bounds.y1;
2473 }
2474 }
2475 else if (layout_changed)
2476 {
2477 no_position_icons = g_list_prepend (no_position_icons, icon);
2478 }
2479 }
2480
2481 if (layout_changed)
2482 {
2483 /* If layout changed, place all the other icons that don't have stored
2484 * positions yet */
2485 no_position_icons = g_list_reverse (no_position_icons);
2486 lay_down_icons (container, no_position_icons, bottom + ICON_PAD_BOTTOM);
2487 }
2488
2489 g_list_free (no_position_icons);
2490}

2495button_event_modifies_selection (GdkEventButton *event)
2496{
2497 return (event->state & (GDK_CONTROL_MASK | GDK_SHIFT_MASK)) != 0;
2498}

2529
2530static gboolean
2531select_range (CajaIconContainer *container,
2532 CajaIcon *icon1,
2533 CajaIcon *icon2,
2534 gboolean unselect_outside_range)
2535{
2536 gboolean selection_changed;
2537 GList *p;
2538 CajaIcon *icon = NULL;
2539 CajaIcon *unmatched_icon;
2540 gboolean select;
2541
2542 selection_changed = FALSE;
2543
2544 unmatched_icon = NULL;
2545 select = FALSE;
2546 for (p = container->details->icons; p != NULL; p = p->next)
2547 {
2548 icon = p->data;
2549
2550 if (unmatched_icon == NULL)
2551 {
2552 if (icon == icon1)
2553 {
2554 unmatched_icon = icon2;
2555 select = TRUE;
2556 }
2557 else if (icon == icon2)
2558 {
2559 unmatched_icon = icon1;
2560 select = TRUE;
2561 }
2562 }
2563
2564 if (select || unselect_outside_range)
2565 {
2566 selection_changed |= icon_set_selected
2567 (container, icon, select);
2568 }
2569
2570 if (unmatched_icon != NULL && icon == unmatched_icon)
2571 {
2572 select = FALSE;
2573 }
2574
2575 }
2576
2577 if (selection_changed && icon2 != NULL)
2578 {
2579 emit_atk_focus_state_change (icon2, TRUE);
2580 }
2581 return selection_changed;
2582}
2583
2584static gboolean
2585select_one_unselect_others (CajaIconContainer *container,
2586 CajaIcon *icon_to_select)
2587{
2588 gboolean selection_changed;
2589 GList *p;
2590 CajaIcon *icon = NULL;
2591
2592 selection_changed = FALSE;
2593
2594 for (p = container->details->icons; p != NULL; p = p->next)
2595 {
2596 icon = p->data;
2597
2598 selection_changed |= icon_set_selected
2599 (container, icon, icon == icon_to_select);
2600 }
2601
2602 if (selection_changed && icon_to_select != NULL)
2603 {
2604 emit_atk_focus_state_change (icon_to_select, TRUE);
2605 reveal_icon (container, icon_to_select);
2606 }
2607 return selection_changed;
2608}
2609
2610static gboolean
2611unselect_all (CajaIconContainer *container)
2612{
2613 return select_one_unselect_others (container, NULL);
2614}
2615
2616void
2617caja_icon_container_move_icon (CajaIconContainer *container,
2618 CajaIcon *icon,
2619 int x, int y,
2620 double scale,
2621 gboolean raise,
2622 gboolean snap,
2623 gboolean update_position)
2624{
2625 CajaIconContainerDetails *details;
2626 gboolean emit_signal;
2627 CajaIconPosition position;
2628
2629 details = container->details;
2630
2631 emit_signal = FALSE;
2632
2633 if (icon == get_icon_being_renamed (container))
2634 {
2635 end_renaming_mode (container, TRUE);
2636 }
2637
2638 if (scale != icon->scale)
2639 {
2640 icon->scale = scale;
2641 caja_icon_container_update_icon (container, icon);
2642 if (update_position)
2643 {
2644 redo_layout (container);
2645 emit_signal = TRUE;
2646 }
2647 }
2648
2649 if (!details->auto_layout && !details->lock_icons_position)
2650 {
2651 if (details->keep_aligned && snap)
2652 {
2653 snap_position (container, icon, &x, &y);
2654 }
2655
2656 if (x != icon->x || y != icon->y)
2657 {
2658 icon_set_position (icon, x, y);
2659 emit_signal = update_position;
2660 }
2661
2662 icon->saved_ltr_x = caja_icon_container_is_layout_rtl (container) ? get_mirror_x_position (container, icon, icon->x) : icon->x;
2663 }
2664
2665 if (emit_signal)
2666 {
2667 position.x = icon->saved_ltr_x;
2668 position.y = icon->y;
2669 position.scale = scale;
2670 g_signal_emit (container,
2671 signals[ICON_POSITION_CHANGED], 0,
2672 icon->data, &position);
2673 }
2674
2675 if (raise)
2676 {
2677 icon_raise (icon);
2678 }
2679
2680 /* FIXME bugzilla.gnome.org 42474:
2681 * Handling of the scroll region is inconsistent here. In
2682 * the scale-changing case, redo_layout is called, which updates the
2683 * scroll region appropriately. In other cases, it's up to the
2684 * caller to make sure the scroll region is updated. This could
2685 * lead to hard-to-track-down bugs.
2686 */
2687}
2688
2689/* Implementation of rubberband selection. */
2690static void
2691rubberband_select (CajaIconContainer *container,
2692 const EelDRect *previous_rect,
2693 const EelDRect *current_rect)
2694{
2695 GList *p;
2696 gboolean selection_changed, is_in, canvas_rect_calculated;
2697 EelIRect canvas_rect;
2698 EelCanvas *canvas;
2699 CajaIcon *icon = NULL;
2700
2701 selection_changed = FALSE;
2702 canvas_rect_calculated = FALSE;
2703
2704 for (p = container->details->icons; p != NULL; p = p->next)
2705 {
2706 icon = p->data;
2707
2708 if (!canvas_rect_calculated)
2709 {
2710 /* Only do this calculation once, since all the canvas items
2711 * we are interating are in the same coordinate space
2712 */
2713 canvas = EEL_CANVAS_ITEM (icon->item)->canvas;
2714 eel_canvas_w2c (canvas,
2715 current_rect->x0,
2716 current_rect->y0,
2717 &canvas_rect.x0,
2718 &canvas_rect.y0);
2719 eel_canvas_w2c (canvas,
2720 current_rect->x1,
2721 current_rect->y1,
2722 &canvas_rect.x1,
2723 &canvas_rect.y1);
2724 canvas_rect_calculated = TRUE;
2725 }
2726
2727 is_in = caja_icon_canvas_item_hit_test_rectangle (icon->item, canvas_rect);
2728
2729 selection_changed |= icon_set_selected
2730 (container, icon,
2731 is_in ^ icon->was_selected_before_rubberband);
2732 }
2733
2734 if (selection_changed)
2735 {
2736 g_signal_emit (container,
2737 signals[SELECTION_CHANGED], 0);
2738 }
2739}
2740
2741static int
2742rubberband_timeout_callback (gpointer data)
2743{
2744 CajaIconContainer *container;
2745 GtkWidget *widget;
2746 CajaIconRubberbandInfo *band_info;
2747 int x, y;
2748 double x1, y1, x2, y2;
2749 double world_x, world_y;
2750 int x_scroll, y_scroll;
2751 int adj_x, adj_y;
2752 GdkDisplay *display;
2753 GdkSeat *seat;
2754 gboolean adj_changed;
2755 GtkAllocation allocation;
2756
2757 EelDRect selection_rect;
2758
2759 widget = GTK_WIDGET (data);
2760 container = CAJA_ICON_CONTAINER (data);
2761 band_info = &container->details->rubberband_info;
2762
2763 g_assert (band_info->timer_id != 0);
2764 g_assert (EEL_IS_CANVAS_RECT (band_info->selection_rectangle) ||
2765 EEL_IS_CANVAS_RECT (band_info->selection_rectangle));
2766
2767 adj_changed = FALSE;
2768 gtk_widget_get_allocation (widget, &allocation);
2769
2770 adj_x = gtk_adjustment_get_value (gtk_scrollable_get_hadjustment (GTK_SCROLLABLE (container)));
2771 if (adj_x != band_info->last_adj_x)
2772 {
2773 band_info->last_adj_x = adj_x;
2774 adj_changed = TRUE;
2775 }
2776
2777 adj_y = gtk_adjustment_get_value (gtk_scrollable_get_vadjustment (GTK_SCROLLABLE (container)));
2778 if (adj_y != band_info->last_adj_y)
2779 {
2780 band_info->last_adj_y = adj_y;
2781 adj_changed = TRUE;
2782 }
2783 display = gtk_widget_get_display (widget);
2784 seat = gdk_display_get_default_seat (display);
2785
2786 gdk_window_get_device_position (gtk_widget_get_window (widget),
2787 gdk_seat_get_pointer (seat),
2788 &x, &y, NULL);
2789
2790 if (x < 0)
2791 {
2792 x_scroll = x;
2793 x = 0;
2794 }
2795 else if (x >= allocation.width)
2796 {
2797 x_scroll = x - allocation.width + 1;
2798 x = allocation.width - 1;
2799 }
2800 else
2801 {
2802 x_scroll = 0;
2803 }
2804
2805 if (y < 0)
2806 {
2807 y_scroll = y;
2808 y = 0;
2809 }
2810 else if (y >= allocation.height)
2811 {
2812 y_scroll = y - allocation.height + 1;
2813 y = allocation.height - 1;
2814 }
2815 else
2816 {
2817 y_scroll = 0;
2818 }
2819
2820 if (y_scroll == 0 && x_scroll == 0
2821 && (int) band_info->prev_x == x && (int) band_info->prev_y == y && !adj_changed)
2822 {
2823 return TRUE;
2824 }
2825
2826 caja_icon_container_scroll (container, x_scroll, y_scroll);
2827
2828 /* Remember to convert from widget to scrolled window coords */
2829 eel_canvas_window_to_world (EEL_CANVAS (container),
2830 x + gtk_adjustment_get_value (gtk_scrollable_get_hadjustment (GTK_SCROLLABLE (container))),
2831 y + gtk_adjustment_get_value (gtk_scrollable_get_vadjustment (GTK_SCROLLABLE (container))),
2832 &world_x, &world_y);
2833
2834 if (world_x < band_info->start_x)
2835 {
2836 x1 = world_x;
2837 x2 = band_info->start_x;
2838 }
2839 else
2840 {
2841 x1 = band_info->start_x;
2842 x2 = world_x;
2843 }
2844
2845 if (world_y < band_info->start_y)
2846 {
2847 y1 = world_y;
2848 y2 = band_info->start_y;
2849 }
2850 else
2851 {
2852 y1 = band_info->start_y;
2853 y2 = world_y;
2854 }
2855
2856 /* Don't let the area of the selection rectangle be empty.
2857 * Aside from the fact that it would be funny when the rectangle disappears,
2858 * this also works around a crash in libart that happens sometimes when a
2859 * zero height rectangle is passed.
2860 */
2861 x2 = MAX (x1 + 1, x2);
2862 y2 = MAX (y1 + 1, y2);
2863
2864 eel_canvas_item_set
2865 (band_info->selection_rectangle,
2866 "x1", x1, "y1", y1,
2867 "x2", x2, "y2", y2,
2868 NULL);
2869
2870 selection_rect.x0 = x1;
2871 selection_rect.y0 = y1;
2872 selection_rect.x1 = x2;
2873 selection_rect.y1 = y2;
2874
2875 rubberband_select (container,
2876 &band_info->prev_rect,
2877 &selection_rect);
2878
2879 band_info->prev_x = x;
2880 band_info->prev_y = y;
2881
2882 band_info->prev_rect = selection_rect;
2883
2884 return TRUE;
2885}
2886
2887/*borrowed from Nemo, makes Caja rubberbanding follow same selectors as Nemo and presumably Nautilus */
2888static void
2889start_rubberbanding (CajaIconContainer *container,
2890 GdkEventButton *event)
2891{
2892 AtkObject *accessible;
2893 CajaIconContainerDetails *details;
2894 CajaIconRubberbandInfo *band_info;
2895 GdkRGBA bg_color, border_color;
2896 GdkRGBA *c;
2897 GList *p;
2898 CajaIcon *icon;
2899 GtkStyleContext *context;
2900
2901 details = container->details;
2902 band_info = &details->rubberband_info;
2903
2904 g_signal_emit (container,
2905 signals[BAND_SELECT_STARTED], 0);
2906
2907 for (p = details->icons; p != NULL; p = p->next) {
2908 icon = p->data;
2909 icon->was_selected_before_rubberband = icon->is_selected;
2910 }
2911
2912 eel_canvas_window_to_world
2913 (EEL_CANVAS (container), event->x, event->y,
2914 &band_info->start_x, &band_info->start_y);
2915
2916 context = gtk_widget_get_style_context (GTK_WIDGET (container));
2917 gtk_style_context_save (context);
2918 gtk_style_context_add_class (context, GTK_STYLE_CLASS_RUBBERBAND);
2919
2920 gtk_style_context_get (context, GTK_STATE_FLAG_NORMAL,
2921 GTK_STYLE_PROPERTY_BACKGROUND_COLOR,
2922 &c, NULL);
2923
2924 bg_color = *c;
2925
2926 gtk_style_context_get (context, GTK_STATE_FLAG_NORMAL,
2927 GTK_STYLE_PROPERTY_BORDER_COLOR,
2928 &c, NULL);
2929
2930 border_color = *c;
2931 gdk_rgba_free (c);
2932
2933 gtk_style_context_restore (context);
2934
2935 band_info->selection_rectangle = eel_canvas_item_new
2936 (eel_canvas_root
2937 (EEL_CANVAS (container)),
2938 EEL_TYPE_CANVAS_RECT,
2939 "x1", band_info->start_x,
2940 "y1", band_info->start_y,
2941 "x2", band_info->start_x,
2942 "y2", band_info->start_y,
2943 "fill_color_rgba", &bg_color,
2944 "outline_color_rgba", &border_color,
2945 "width_pixels", 1,
2946 NULL);
2947
2948 accessible = atk_gobject_accessible_for_object
2949 (G_OBJECT (band_info->selection_rectangle));
2950 atk_object_set_name (accessible, "selection");
2951 atk_object_set_description (accessible, _("The selection rectangle"));
2952
2953 band_info->prev_x = event->x - gtk_adjustment_get_value (gtk_scrollable_get_hadjustment (GTK_SCROLLABLE (container)));
2954 band_info->prev_y = event->y - gtk_adjustment_get_value (gtk_scrollable_get_vadjustment (GTK_SCROLLABLE (container)));
2955
2956 band_info->active = TRUE;
2957
2958 if (band_info->timer_id == 0) {
2959 band_info->timer_id = g_timeout_add
2960 (RUBBERBAND_TIMEOUT_INTERVAL,
2961 rubberband_timeout_callback,
2962 container);
2963 }
2964
2965 eel_canvas_item_grab (band_info->selection_rectangle,
2966 (GDK_POINTER_MOTION_MASK
2967 | GDK_BUTTON_RELEASE_MASK
2968 | GDK_SCROLL_MASK),
2969 NULL,
2970 (GdkEvent *)event);
2971}
2972
2973static void
2974stop_rubberbanding (CajaIconContainer *container)
2975{
2976 CajaIconRubberbandInfo *band_info;
2977 GList *icons;
2978
2979 band_info = &container->details->rubberband_info;
2980
2981 g_assert (band_info->timer_id != 0);
2982 g_source_remove (band_info->timer_id);
2983 band_info->timer_id = 0;
2984
2985 band_info->active = FALSE;
2986
2987 /* Destroy this canvas item; the parent will unref it. */
2988 eel_canvas_item_ungrab (band_info->selection_rectangle);
2989 eel_canvas_item_destroy (band_info->selection_rectangle);
2990 band_info->selection_rectangle = NULL;
2991
2992 /* if only one item has been selected, use it as range
2993 * selection base (cf. handle_icon_button_press) */
2994 icons = caja_icon_container_get_selected_icons (container);
2995 if (g_list_length (icons) == 1)
2996 {
2997 container->details->range_selection_base_icon = icons->data;
2998 }
2999 g_list_free (icons);
3000
3001 g_signal_emit (container,
3002 signals[BAND_SELECT_ENDED], 0);
3003}

3005/* Keyboard navigation. */
3006
3007typedef gboolean (* IsBetterIconFunction) (CajaIconContainer *container,
3008 CajaIcon *start_icon,
3009 CajaIcon *best_so_far,
3010 CajaIcon *candidate,
3011 void *data);
3012
3013static CajaIcon *
3014find_best_icon (CajaIconContainer *container,
3015 CajaIcon *start_icon,
3016 IsBetterIconFunction function,
3017 void *data)
3018{
3019 GList *p;
3020 CajaIcon *best, *candidate;
3021
3022 best = NULL;
3023 for (p = container->details->icons; p != NULL; p = p->next)
3024 {
3025 candidate = p->data;
3026
3027 if (candidate != start_icon)
3028 {
3029 if ((* function) (container, start_icon, best, candidate, data))
3030 {
3031 best = candidate;
3032 }
3033 }
3034 }
3035 return best;
3036}
3037
3038static CajaIcon *
3039find_best_selected_icon (CajaIconContainer *container,
3040 CajaIcon *start_icon,
3041 IsBetterIconFunction function,
3042 void *data)
3043{
3044 GList *p;
3045 CajaIcon *best, *candidate;
3046
3047 best = NULL;
3048 for (p = container->details->icons; p != NULL; p = p->next)
3049 {
3050 candidate = p->data;
3051
3052 if (candidate != start_icon && candidate->is_selected)
3053 {
3054 if ((* function) (container, start_icon, best, candidate, data))
3055 {
3056 best = candidate;
3057 }
3058 }
3059 }
3060 return best;
3061}
3062
3063static int
3064compare_icons_by_uri (CajaIconContainer *container,
3065 CajaIcon *icon_a,
3066 CajaIcon *icon_b)
3067{
3068 char *uri_a, *uri_b;
3069 int result;
3070
3071 g_assert (CAJA_IS_ICON_CONTAINER (container));
3072 g_assert (icon_a != NULL);
3073 g_assert (icon_b != NULL);
3074 g_assert (icon_a != icon_b);
3075
3076 uri_a = caja_icon_container_get_icon_uri (container, icon_a);
3077 uri_b = caja_icon_container_get_icon_uri (container, icon_b);
3078 result = strcmp (uri_a, uri_b);
3079 g_assert (result != 0);
3080 g_free (uri_a);
3081 g_free (uri_b);
3082
3083 return result;
3084}
3085
3086static int
3087get_cmp_point_x (CajaIconContainer *container,
3088 EelDRect icon_rect)
3089{
3090 if (container->details->label_position == CAJA_ICON_LABEL_POSITION_BESIDE)
3091 {
3092 if (gtk_widget_get_direction (GTK_WIDGET (container)) == GTK_TEXT_DIR_RTL)
3093 {
3094 return icon_rect.x0;
3095 }
3096 else
3097 {
3098 return icon_rect.x1;
3099 }
3100 }
3101 else
3102 {
3103 return (icon_rect.x0 + icon_rect.x1) / 2;
3104 }
3105}
3106
3107static int
3108get_cmp_point_y (CajaIconContainer *container,
3109 EelDRect icon_rect)
3110{
3111 if (container->details->label_position == CAJA_ICON_LABEL_POSITION_BESIDE)
3112 {
3113 return (icon_rect.y0 + icon_rect.y1)/2;
3114 }
3115 else
3116 {
3117 return icon_rect.y1;
3118 }
3119}

3121static int
3122compare_icons_horizontal (CajaIconContainer *container,
3123 CajaIcon *icon_a,
3124 CajaIcon *icon_b)
3125{
3126 EelDRect world_rect;
3127 int ax, bx;
3128
3129 world_rect = caja_icon_canvas_item_get_icon_rectangle (icon_a->item);
3130 eel_canvas_w2c
3131 (EEL_CANVAS (container),
3132 get_cmp_point_x (container, world_rect),
3133 get_cmp_point_y (container, world_rect),
3134 &ax,
3135 NULL);
3136 world_rect = caja_icon_canvas_item_get_icon_rectangle (icon_b->item);
3137 eel_canvas_w2c
3138 (EEL_CANVAS (container),
3139 get_cmp_point_x (container, world_rect),
3140 get_cmp_point_y (container, world_rect),
3141 &bx,
3142 NULL);
3143
3144 if (ax < bx)
3145 {
3146 return -1;
3147 }
3148 if (ax > bx)
3149 {
3150 return +1;
3151 }
3152 return 0;
3153}

3198 eel_canvas_w2c
3199 (EEL_CANVAS (container),
3200 get_cmp_point_x (container, world_rect),

3210 &by);

3273static gboolean
3274leftmost_in_top_row (CajaIconContainer *container,
3275 CajaIcon *start_icon,
3276 CajaIcon *best_so_far,
3277 CajaIcon *candidate,
3278 void *data)
3279{
3280 if (best_so_far == NULL)
3281 {
3282 return TRUE;
3283 }
3284 return compare_icons_vertical_first (container, best_so_far, candidate) > 0;
3285}

3287static gboolean

3289 CajaIcon *start_icon,
3290 CajaIcon *best_so_far,
3291 CajaIcon *candidate,
3292 void *data)
3293{
3294 if (best_so_far == NULL)
3295 {
3296 return TRUE;
3297 }
3298 return ((compare_icons_vertical (container, best_so_far, candidate) > 0) &&
3299 (compare_icons_horizontal (container, best_so_far, candidate) < 0));
3300}

3316static int

3318 CajaIcon *icon)
3319{

3321

3325 {

3327 }

3329 {
