3354static gboolean
3355same_row_right_side_leftmost (CajaIconContainer *container,
3356 CajaIcon *start_icon,
3357 CajaIcon *best_so_far,
3358 CajaIcon *candidate,
3359 void *data)
3360{
3361 /* Candidates not on the start row do not qualify. */
3362 if (compare_with_start_row (container, candidate) != 0)
3363 {
3364 return FALSE;
3365 }
3366
3367 /* Candidates that are farther right lose out. */
3368 if (best_so_far != NULL)
3369 {
3370 if (compare_icons_horizontal_first (container,
3371 best_so_far,
3372 candidate) < 0)
3373 {
3374 return FALSE;
3375 }
3376 }
3377
3378 /* Candidate to the left of the start do not qualify. */
3379 if (compare_icons_horizontal_first (container,
3380 candidate,
3381 start_icon) <= 0)
3382 {
3383 return FALSE;
3384 }
3385
3386 return TRUE;
3387}
3388
3389static gboolean
3390same_row_left_side_rightmost (CajaIconContainer *container,
3391 CajaIcon *start_icon,
3392 CajaIcon *best_so_far,
3393 CajaIcon *candidate,
3394 void *data)
3395{
3396 /* Candidates not on the start row do not qualify. */
3397 if (compare_with_start_row (container, candidate) != 0)
3398 {
3399 return FALSE;
3400 }
3401
3402 /* Candidates that are farther left lose out. */
3403 if (best_so_far != NULL)
3404 {
3405 if (compare_icons_horizontal_first (container,
3406 best_so_far,
3407 candidate) > 0)
3408 {
3409 return FALSE;
3410 }
3411 }
3412
3413 /* Candidate to the right of the start do not qualify. */
3414 if (compare_icons_horizontal_first (container,
3415 candidate,
3416 start_icon) >= 0)
3417 {
3418 return FALSE;
3419 }
3420
3421 return TRUE;
3422}

3424static gboolean
3425next_row_leftmost (CajaIconContainer *container,
3426 CajaIcon *start_icon,
3427 CajaIcon *best_so_far,
3428 CajaIcon *candidate,
3429 void *data)
3430{
3431 /* sort out icons that are not below the current row */
3432 if (compare_with_start_row (container, candidate) >= 0)
3433 {
3434 return FALSE;
3435 }
3436
3437 if (best_so_far != NULL)
3438 {
3439 if (compare_icons_vertical_first (container,
3440 best_so_far,
3441 candidate) > 0)
3442 {
3443 /* candidate is above best choice, but below the current row */
3444 return TRUE;
3445 }
3446
3447 if (compare_icons_horizontal_first (container,
3448 best_so_far,
3449 candidate) > 0)
3450 {
3451 return TRUE;
3452 }
3453 }
3454
3455 return best_so_far == NULL;
3456}

3560static gboolean
3561same_column_above_lowest (CajaIconContainer *container,
3562 CajaIcon *start_icon,
3563 CajaIcon *best_so_far,
3564 CajaIcon *candidate,
3565 void *data)
3566{
3567 /* Candidates not on the start column do not qualify. */
3568 if (compare_with_start_column (container, candidate) != 0)
3569 {
3570 return FALSE;
3571 }
3572
3573 /* Candidates that are higher lose out. */
3574 if (best_so_far != NULL)
3575 {
3576 if (compare_icons_vertical_first (container,
3577 best_so_far,
3578 candidate) > 0)
3579 {
3580 return FALSE;
3581 }
3582 }
3583
3584 /* Candidates below the start do not qualify. */
3585 if (compare_icons_vertical_first (container,
3586 candidate,
3587 start_icon) >= 0)
3588 {
3589 return FALSE;
3590 }
3591
3592 return TRUE;
3593}
3594
3595static gboolean
3596same_column_below_highest (CajaIconContainer *container,
3597 CajaIcon *start_icon,
3598 CajaIcon *best_so_far,
3599 CajaIcon *candidate,
3600 void *data)
3601{
3602 /* Candidates not on the start column do not qualify. */
3603 if (compare_with_start_column (container, candidate) != 0)
3604 {
3605 return FALSE;
3606 }
3607
3608 /* Candidates that are lower lose out. */
3609 if (best_so_far != NULL)
3610 {
3611 if (compare_icons_vertical_first (container,
3612 best_so_far,
3613 candidate) < 0)
3614 {
3615 return FALSE;
3616 }
3617 }
3618
3619 /* Candidates above the start do not qualify. */
3620 if (compare_icons_vertical_first (container,
3621 candidate,
3622 start_icon) <= 0)
3623 {
3624 return FALSE;
3625 }
3626
3627 return TRUE;
3628}
3629
3630static gboolean
3631previous_column_highest (CajaIconContainer *container,
3632 CajaIcon *start_icon,
3633 CajaIcon *best_so_far,
3634 CajaIcon *candidate,
3635 void *data)
3636{
3637 /* sort out icons that are not before the current column */
3638 if (compare_with_start_column (container, candidate) <= 0)
3639 {
3640 return FALSE;
3641 }
3642
3643 if (best_so_far != NULL)
3644 {
3645 if (compare_icons_horizontal (container,
3646 best_so_far,
3647 candidate) < 0)
3648 {
3649 /* candidate is right of the best choice, but left of the current column */
3650 return TRUE;
3651 }
3652
3653 if (compare_icons_vertical (container,
3654 best_so_far,
3655 candidate) > 0)
3656 {
3657 return TRUE;
3658 }
3659 }
3660
3661 return best_so_far == NULL;
3662}
3663
3664static gboolean
3665next_column_highest (CajaIconContainer *container,
3666 CajaIcon *start_icon,
3667 CajaIcon *best_so_far,
3668 CajaIcon *candidate,
3669 void *data)
3670{
3671 /* sort out icons that are not after the current column */
3672 if (compare_with_start_column (container, candidate) >= 0)
3673 {
3674 return FALSE;
3675 }
3676
3677 if (best_so_far != NULL)
3678 {
3679 if (compare_icons_horizontal_first (container,
3680 best_so_far,
3681 candidate) > 0)
3682 {
3683 /* candidate is left of the best choice, but right of the current column */
3684 return TRUE;
3685 }
3686
3687 if (compare_icons_vertical_first (container,
3688 best_so_far,
3689 candidate) > 0)
3690 {
3691 return TRUE;
3692 }
3693 }
3694
3695 return best_so_far == NULL;
3696}
3697
3698static gboolean
3699previous_column_lowest (CajaIconContainer *container,
3700 CajaIcon *start_icon,
3701 CajaIcon *best_so_far,
3702 CajaIcon *candidate,
3703 void *data)
3704{
3705 /* sort out icons that are not before the current column */
3706 if (compare_with_start_column (container, candidate) <= 0)
3707 {
3708 return FALSE;
3709 }
3710
3711 if (best_so_far != NULL)
3712 {
3713 if (compare_icons_horizontal_first (container,
3714 best_so_far,
3715 candidate) < 0)
3716 {
3717 /* candidate is right of the best choice, but left of the current column */
3718 return TRUE;
3719 }
3720
3721 if (compare_icons_vertical_first (container,
3722 best_so_far,
3723 candidate) < 0)
3724 {
3725 return TRUE;
3726 }
3727 }
3728
3729 return best_so_far == NULL;
3730}
3731
3732static gboolean
3733last_column_lowest (CajaIconContainer *container,
3734 CajaIcon *start_icon,
3735 CajaIcon *best_so_far,
3736 CajaIcon *candidate,
3737 void *data)
3738{
3739 if (best_so_far == NULL)
3740 {
3741 return TRUE;
3742 }
3743 return compare_icons_horizontal_first (container, best_so_far, candidate) < 0;
3744}
3745
3746static gboolean
3747closest_in_90_degrees (CajaIconContainer *container,
3748 CajaIcon *start_icon,
3749 CajaIcon *best_so_far,
3750 CajaIcon *candidate,
3751 void *data)
3752{
3753 EelDRect world_rect;
3754 int x, y;
3755 int dx, dy;
3756 int dist;
3757 int *best_dist;
3758
3759 world_rect = caja_icon_canvas_item_get_icon_rectangle (candidate->item);
3760 eel_canvas_w2c
3761 (EEL_CANVAS (container),
3762 get_cmp_point_x (container, world_rect),
3763 get_cmp_point_y (container, world_rect),
3764 &x,
3765 &y);
3766
3767 dx = x - container->details->arrow_key_start_x;
3768 dy = y - container->details->arrow_key_start_y;
3769
3770 switch (container->details->arrow_key_direction)
3771 {
3772 case GTK_DIR_UP:
3773 if (dy > 0 ||
3774 ABS(dx) > ABS(dy))
3775 {
3776 return FALSE;
3777 }
3778 break;
3779 case GTK_DIR_DOWN:
3780 if (dy < 0 ||
3781 ABS(dx) > ABS(dy))
3782 {
3783 return FALSE;
3784 }
3785 break;
3786 case GTK_DIR_LEFT:
3787 if (dx > 0 ||
3788 ABS(dy) > ABS(dx))
3789 {
3790 return FALSE;
3791 }
3792 break;
3793 case GTK_DIR_RIGHT:
3794 if (dx < 0 ||
3795 ABS(dy) > ABS(dx))
3796 {
3797 return FALSE;
3798 }
3799 break;
3800 default:
3801 g_assert_not_reached();
3802 }
3803
3804 dist = dx*dx + dy*dy;
3805 best_dist = data;
3806
3807 if (best_so_far == NULL)
3808 {
3809 *best_dist = dist;
3810 return TRUE;
3811 }
3812
3813 if (dist < *best_dist)
3814 {
3815 *best_dist = dist;
3816 return TRUE;
3817 }
3818
3819 return FALSE;
3820}
3821
3822static EelDRect
3823get_rubberband (CajaIcon *icon1,
3824 CajaIcon *icon2)
3825{
3826 EelDRect rect1;
3827 EelDRect rect2;
3828 EelDRect ret;
3829
3830 eel_canvas_item_get_bounds (EEL_CANVAS_ITEM (icon1->item),
3831 &rect1.x0, &rect1.y0,
3832 &rect1.x1, &rect1.y1);
3833 eel_canvas_item_get_bounds (EEL_CANVAS_ITEM (icon2->item),
3834 &rect2.x0, &rect2.y0,
3835 &rect2.x1, &rect2.y1);
3836
3837 eel_drect_union (&ret, &rect1, &rect2);
3838
3839 return ret;
3840}
3841
3842static void
3843keyboard_move_to (CajaIconContainer *container,
3844 CajaIcon *icon,
3845 CajaIcon *from,
3846 GdkEventKey *event)
3847{
3848 if (icon == NULL)
3849 {
3850 return;
3851 }
3852
3853 if (event != NULL &&
3854 (event->state & GDK_CONTROL_MASK) != 0 &&
3855 (event->state & GDK_SHIFT_MASK) == 0)
3856 {
3857 /* Move the keyboard focus. Use Control modifier
3858 * rather than Alt to avoid Sawfish conflict.
3859 */
3860 set_keyboard_focus (container, icon);
3861 container->details->keyboard_rubberband_start = NULL;
3862 }
3863 else if (event != NULL &&
3864 ((event->state & GDK_CONTROL_MASK) != 0 ||
3865 !container->details->auto_layout) &&
3866 (event->state & GDK_SHIFT_MASK) != 0)
3867 {
3868 /* Do rubberband selection */
3869 EelDRect rect;
3870
3871 if (from && !container->details->keyboard_rubberband_start)
3872 {
3873 set_keyboard_rubberband_start (container, from);
3874 }
3875
3876 set_keyboard_focus (container, icon);
3877
3878 if (icon && container->details->keyboard_rubberband_start)
3879 {
3880 rect = get_rubberband (container->details->keyboard_rubberband_start,
3881 icon);
3882 rubberband_select (container, NULL, &rect);
3883 }
3884 }
3885 else if (event != NULL &&
3886 (event->state & GDK_CONTROL_MASK) == 0 &&
3887 (event->state & GDK_SHIFT_MASK) != 0)
3888 {
3889 /* Select range */
3890 CajaIcon *start_icon;
3891
3892 start_icon = container->details->range_selection_base_icon;
3893 if (start_icon == NULL || !start_icon->is_selected)
3894 {
3895 start_icon = icon;
3896 container->details->range_selection_base_icon = icon;
3897 }
3898
3899 set_keyboard_focus (container, icon);
3900
3901 if (select_range (container, start_icon, icon, TRUE))
3902 {
3903 g_signal_emit (container,
3904 signals[SELECTION_CHANGED], 0);
3905 }
3906 }
3907 else
3908 {
3909 /* Select icons and get rid of the special keyboard focus. */
3910 clear_keyboard_focus (container);
3911 clear_keyboard_rubberband_start (container);
3912
3913 container->details->range_selection_base_icon = icon;
3914 if (select_one_unselect_others (container, icon))
3915 {
3916 g_signal_emit (container,
3917 signals[SELECTION_CHANGED], 0);
3918 }
3919 }
3920 schedule_keyboard_icon_reveal (container, icon);
3921}
3922
3923static void
3924keyboard_home (CajaIconContainer *container,
3925 GdkEventKey *event)
3926{
3927 CajaIcon *from;
3928 CajaIcon *to;
3929
3930 /* Home selects the first icon.
3931 * Control-Home sets the keyboard focus to the first icon.
3932 */
3933
3934 from = find_best_selected_icon (container, NULL,
3935 rightmost_in_bottom_row,
3936 NULL);
3937 to = find_best_icon (container, NULL, leftmost_in_top_row, NULL);
3938
3939 keyboard_move_to (container, to, from, event);
3940}
3941
3942static void
3943keyboard_end (CajaIconContainer *container,
3944 GdkEventKey *event)
3945{
3946 CajaIcon *to;
3947 CajaIcon *from;
3948
3949 /* End selects the last icon.
3950 * Control-End sets the keyboard focus to the last icon.
3951 */
3952 from = find_best_selected_icon (container, NULL,
3953 leftmost_in_top_row,
3954 NULL);
3955 to = find_best_icon (container, NULL,
3956 caja_icon_container_is_layout_vertical (container) ?
3957 last_column_lowest :
3958 rightmost_in_bottom_row,
3959 NULL);
3960
3961 keyboard_move_to (container, to, from, event);
3962}
3963
3964static void
3965record_arrow_key_start (CajaIconContainer *container,
3966 CajaIcon *icon,
3967 GtkDirectionType direction)
3968{
3969 EelDRect world_rect;
3970
3971 world_rect = caja_icon_canvas_item_get_icon_rectangle (icon->item);
3972 eel_canvas_w2c
3973 (EEL_CANVAS (container),
3974 get_cmp_point_x (container, world_rect),
3975 get_cmp_point_y (container, world_rect),
3976 &container->details->arrow_key_start_x,
3977 &container->details->arrow_key_start_y);
3978 container->details->arrow_key_direction = direction;
3979}
3980
3981static void
3982keyboard_arrow_key (CajaIconContainer *container,
3983 GdkEventKey *event,
3984 GtkDirectionType direction,
3985 IsBetterIconFunction better_start,
3986 IsBetterIconFunction empty_start,
3987 IsBetterIconFunction better_destination,
3988 IsBetterIconFunction better_destination_fallback,
3989 IsBetterIconFunction better_destination_fallback_fallback,
3990 IsBetterIconFunction better_destination_manual)
3991{
3992 CajaIcon *from;
3993 CajaIcon *to;
3994 int data;
3995
3996 /* Chose the icon to start with.
3997 * If we have a keyboard focus, start with it.
3998 * Otherwise, use the single selected icon.
3999 * If there's multiple selection, use the icon farthest toward the end.
4000 */
4001
4002 from = container->details->keyboard_focus;
4003
4004 if (from == NULL)
4005 {
4006 if (has_multiple_selection (container))
4007 {
4008 if (all_selected (container))
4009 {
4010 from = find_best_selected_icon
4011 (container, NULL,
4012 empty_start, NULL);
4013 }
4014 else
4015 {
4016 from = find_best_selected_icon
4017 (container, NULL,
4018 better_start, NULL);
4019 }
4020 }
4021 else
4022 {
4023 from = get_first_selected_icon (container);
4024 }
4025 }
4026
4027 /* If there's no icon, select the icon farthest toward the end.
4028 * If there is an icon, select the next icon based on the arrow direction.
4029 */
4030 if (from == NULL)
4031 {
4032 to = from = find_best_icon
4033 (container, NULL,
4034 empty_start, NULL);
4035 }
4036 else
4037 {
4038 record_arrow_key_start (container, from, direction);
4039
4040 to = find_best_icon
4041 (container, from,
4042 container->details->auto_layout ? better_destination : better_destination_manual,
4043 &data);
4044
4045 /* Wrap around to next/previous row/column */
4046 if (to == NULL &&
4047 better_destination_fallback != NULL) {
4048 to = find_best_icon
4049 (container, from,
4050 better_destination_fallback,
4051 &data);
4052 }
4053
4054 /* With a layout like
4055 * 1 2 3
4056 * 4
4057 * (horizontal layout)
4058 *
4059 * or
4060 *
4061 * 1 4
4062 * 2
4063 * 3
4064 * (vertical layout)
4065 *
4066 * * pressing down for any of 1,2,3 (horizontal layout)
4067 * * pressing right for any of 1,2,3 (vertical layout)
4068 *
4069 * Should select 4.
4070 */
4071 if (to == NULL &&
4072 container->details->auto_layout &&
4073 better_destination_fallback_fallback != NULL)
4074 {
4075 to = find_best_icon
4076 (container, from,
4077 better_destination_fallback_fallback,
4078 &data);
4079 }
4080
4081 if (to == NULL)
4082 {
4083 to = from;
4084 }
4085
4086 }
4087
4088 keyboard_move_to (container, to, from, event);
4089}
4090
4091static gboolean
4092is_rectangle_selection_event (GdkEventKey *event)
4093{
4094 return (event->state & GDK_CONTROL_MASK) != 0 &&
4095 (event->state & GDK_SHIFT_MASK) != 0;
4096}
4097
4098static void
4099keyboard_right (CajaIconContainer *container,
4100 GdkEventKey *event)
4101{
4102 IsBetterIconFunction fallback;
4103 IsBetterIconFunction next_column_fallback;
4104
4105 fallback = NULL;
4106 if (container->details->auto_layout &&
4107 !caja_icon_container_is_layout_vertical (container) &&
4108 !is_rectangle_selection_event (event))
4109 {
4110 fallback = next_row_leftmost;
4111 }
4112
4113 next_column_fallback = NULL;
4114 if (caja_icon_container_is_layout_vertical (container) &&
4115 gtk_widget_get_direction (GTK_WIDGET (container)) != GTK_TEXT_DIR_RTL)
4116 {
4117 next_column_fallback = next_column_bottommost;
4118 }
4119
4120 /* Right selects the next icon in the same row.
4121 * Control-Right sets the keyboard focus to the next icon in the same row.
4122 */
4123 keyboard_arrow_key (container,
4124 event,
4125 GTK_DIR_RIGHT,
4126 rightmost_in_bottom_row,
4127 caja_icon_container_is_layout_rtl (container) ?
4128 rightmost_in_top_row : leftmost_in_top_row,
4129 same_row_right_side_leftmost,
4130 fallback,
4131 next_column_fallback,
4132 closest_in_90_degrees);
4133}
4134
4135static void
4136keyboard_left (CajaIconContainer *container,
4137 GdkEventKey *event)
4138{
4139 IsBetterIconFunction fallback;
4140 IsBetterIconFunction previous_column_fallback;
4141
4142 fallback = NULL;
4143 if (container->details->auto_layout &&
4144 !caja_icon_container_is_layout_vertical (container) &&
4145 !is_rectangle_selection_event (event))
4146 {
4147 fallback = previous_row_rightmost;
4148 }
4149
4150 previous_column_fallback = NULL;
4151 if (caja_icon_container_is_layout_vertical (container) &&
4152 gtk_widget_get_direction (GTK_WIDGET (container)) == GTK_TEXT_DIR_RTL)
4153 {
4154 previous_column_fallback = previous_column_lowest;
4155 }
4156
4157 /* Left selects the next icon in the same row.
4158 * Control-Left sets the keyboard focus to the next icon in the same row.
4159 */
4160 keyboard_arrow_key (container,
4161 event,
4162 GTK_DIR_LEFT,
4163 rightmost_in_bottom_row,
4164 caja_icon_container_is_layout_rtl (container) ?
4165 rightmost_in_top_row : leftmost_in_top_row,
4166 same_row_left_side_rightmost,
4167 fallback,
4168 previous_column_fallback,
4169 closest_in_90_degrees);
4170}
4171
4172static void
4173keyboard_down (CajaIconContainer *container,
4174 GdkEventKey *event)
4175{
4176 IsBetterIconFunction fallback;
4177 IsBetterIconFunction next_row_fallback;
4178
4179 fallback = NULL;
4180 if (container->details->auto_layout &&
4181 caja_icon_container_is_layout_vertical (container) &&
4182 !is_rectangle_selection_event (event))
4183 {
4184 if (gtk_widget_get_direction (GTK_WIDGET (container)) == GTK_TEXT_DIR_RTL)
4185 {
4186 fallback = previous_column_highest;
4187 }
4188 else
4189 {
4190 fallback = next_column_highest;
4191 }
4192 }
4193
4194 next_row_fallback = NULL;
4195 if (!caja_icon_container_is_layout_vertical (container))
4196 {
4197 if (gtk_widget_get_direction (GTK_WIDGET (container)) == GTK_TEXT_DIR_RTL)
4198 {
4199 next_row_fallback = next_row_leftmost;
4200 }
4201 else
4202 {
4203 next_row_fallback = next_row_rightmost;
4204 }
4205 }
4206
4207 /* Down selects the next icon in the same column.
4208 * Control-Down sets the keyboard focus to the next icon in the same column.
4209 */
4210 keyboard_arrow_key (container,
4211 event,
4212 GTK_DIR_DOWN,
4213 rightmost_in_bottom_row,
4214 caja_icon_container_is_layout_rtl (container) ?
4215 rightmost_in_top_row : leftmost_in_top_row,
4216 same_column_below_highest,
4217 fallback,
4218 next_row_fallback,
4219 closest_in_90_degrees);
4220}

4222static void
4223keyboard_up (CajaIconContainer *container,
4224 GdkEventKey *event)
4225{
4226 IsBetterIconFunction fallback;
4227
4228 fallback = NULL;
4229 if (container->details->auto_layout &&
4230 caja_icon_container_is_layout_vertical (container) &&
4231 !is_rectangle_selection_event (event))
4232 {
4233 if (gtk_widget_get_direction (GTK_WIDGET (container)) == GTK_TEXT_DIR_RTL)
4234 {
4235 fallback = next_column_bottommost;
4236 }
4237 else
4238 {
4239 fallback = previous_column_lowest;
4240 }
4241 }
4242
4243 /* Up selects the next icon in the same column.
4244 * Control-Up sets the keyboard focus to the next icon in the same column.
4245 */
4246 keyboard_arrow_key (container,
4247 event,
4248 GTK_DIR_UP,
4249 rightmost_in_bottom_row,
4250 caja_icon_container_is_layout_rtl (container) ?
4251 rightmost_in_top_row : leftmost_in_top_row,
4252 same_column_above_lowest,
4253 fallback,
4254 NULL,
4255 closest_in_90_degrees);
4256}
4257
4258static void
4259keyboard_space (CajaIconContainer *container,
4260 GdkEventKey *event)
4261{
4262 CajaIcon *icon;
4263
4264 if (!has_selection (container) &&
4265 container->details->keyboard_focus != NULL)
4266 {
4267 keyboard_move_to (container,
4268 container->details->keyboard_focus,
4269 NULL, NULL);
4270 }
4271 else if ((event->state & GDK_CONTROL_MASK) != 0 &&
4272 (event->state & GDK_SHIFT_MASK) == 0)
4273 {
4274 /* Control-space toggles the selection state of the current icon. */
4275 if (container->details->keyboard_focus != NULL)
4276 {
4277 icon_toggle_selected (container, container->details->keyboard_focus);
4278 g_signal_emit (container, signals[SELECTION_CHANGED], 0);
4279 if (container->details->keyboard_focus->is_selected)
4280 {
4281 container->details->range_selection_base_icon = container->details->keyboard_focus;
4282 }
4283 }
4284 else
4285 {
4286 icon = find_best_selected_icon (container,
4287 NULL,
4288 leftmost_in_top_row,
4289 NULL);
4290 if (icon == NULL)
4291 {
4292 icon = find_best_icon (container,
4293 NULL,
4294 leftmost_in_top_row,
4295 NULL);
4296 }
4297 if (icon != NULL)
4298 {
4299 set_keyboard_focus (container, icon);
4300 }
4301 }
4302 }
4303 else if ((event->state & GDK_SHIFT_MASK) != 0)
4304 {
4305 activate_selected_items_alternate (container, NULL);
4306 }
4307 else
4308 {
4309 activate_selected_items (container);
4310 }
4311}
4312
4313/* look for the first icon that matches the longest part of a given
4314 * search pattern
4315 */
4316typedef struct
4317{
4318 gunichar *name;
4319 int last_match_length;
4320} BestNameMatch;
4321
4322#ifndef TAB_NAVIGATION_DISABLED
4323static void
4324select_previous_or_next_icon (CajaIconContainer *container,
4325 gboolean next,
4326 GdkEventKey *event)
4327{
4328 CajaIcon *icon;
4329 const GList *item;
4330
4331 item = NULL;
4332 /* Chose the icon to start with.
4333 * If we have a keyboard focus, start with it.
4334 * Otherwise, use the single selected icon.
4335 */
4336 icon = container->details->keyboard_focus;
4337 if (icon == NULL)
4338 {
4339 icon = get_first_selected_icon (container);
4340 }
4341
4342 if (icon != NULL)
4343 {
4344 /* must have at least @icon in the list */
4345 g_assert (container->details->icons != NULL);
4346 item = g_list_find (container->details->icons, icon);
4347 g_assert (item != NULL);
4348
4349 item = next ? item->next : item->prev;
4350 if (item == NULL)
4351 {
4352 item = next ? g_list_first (container->details->icons) : g_list_last (container->details->icons);
4353 }
4354
4355 }
4356 else if (container->details->icons != NULL)
4357 {
4358 /* no selection yet, pick the first or last item to select */
4359 item = next ? g_list_first (container->details->icons) : g_list_last (container->details->icons);
4360 }
4361
4362 icon = (item != NULL) ? item->data : NULL;
4363
4364 if (icon != NULL)
4365 {
4366 keyboard_move_to (container, icon, NULL, event);
4367 }
4368}
4369#endif
4370
4371static void
4372destroy (GtkWidget *object)
4373{
4374 CajaIconContainer *container;
4375
4376 container = CAJA_ICON_CONTAINER (object);
4377
4378 caja_icon_container_clear (container);
4379
4380 if (container->details->rubberband_info.timer_id != 0)
4381 {
4382 g_source_remove (container->details->rubberband_info.timer_id);
4383 container->details->rubberband_info.timer_id = 0;
4384 }
4385
4386 if (container->details->idle_id != 0)
4387 {
4388 g_source_remove (container->details->idle_id);
4389 container->details->idle_id = 0;
4390 }
4391
4392 if (container->details->stretch_idle_id != 0)
4393 {
4394 g_source_remove (container->details->stretch_idle_id);
4395 container->details->stretch_idle_id = 0;
4396 }
4397
4398 if (container->details->align_idle_id != 0)
4399 {
4400 g_source_remove (container->details->align_idle_id);
4401 container->details->align_idle_id = 0;
4402 }
4403
4404 if (container->details->selection_changed_id != 0)
4405 {
4406 g_source_remove (container->details->selection_changed_id);
4407 container->details->selection_changed_id = 0;
4408 }
4409
4410 if (container->details->size_allocation_count_id != 0)
4411 {
4412 g_source_remove (container->details->size_allocation_count_id);
4413 container->details->size_allocation_count_id = 0;
4414 }
4415
4416 /* destroy interactive search dialog */
4417 if (container->details->search_window)
4418 {
4419 /*current GTK docs do not advise calling gtk_widget_destroy on child widgets
4420 *gtk_widget_destroy (container->details->search_window);
4421 *also note that GtkContainer destroys it's child widgets when it is destroyed
4422 */
4423 container->details->search_window = NULL;
4424 container->details->search_entry = NULL;
4425 if (container->details->typeselect_flush_timeout)
4426 {
4427 g_source_remove (container->details->typeselect_flush_timeout);
4428 container->details->typeselect_flush_timeout = 0;
4429 }
4430 }
4431
4432 GTK_WIDGET_CLASS (caja_icon_container_parent_class)->destroy (object);
4433}
4434
4435static void
4436finalize (GObject *object)
4437{
4438 CajaIconContainerDetails *details;
4439
4440 details = CAJA_ICON_CONTAINER (object)->details;
4441
4442 g_signal_handlers_disconnect_by_func (caja_icon_view_preferences,
4443 text_ellipsis_limit_changed_container_callback,
4444 object);
4445 g_signal_handlers_disconnect_by_func (caja_desktop_preferences,
4446 text_ellipsis_limit_changed_container_callback,
4447 object);
4448
4449 g_hash_table_destroy (details->icon_set);
4450 details->icon_set = NULL;
4451
4452 g_free (details->font);
4453
4454 if (details->a11y_item_action_queue != NULL)
4455 {
4456 while (!g_queue_is_empty (details->a11y_item_action_queue))
4457 {
4458 g_free (g_queue_pop_head (details->a11y_item_action_queue));
4459 }
4460 g_queue_free (details->a11y_item_action_queue);
4461 }
4462 if (details->a11y_item_action_idle_handler != 0)
4463 {
4464 g_source_remove (details->a11y_item_action_idle_handler);
4465 }
4466
4467 g_free (details);
4468
4469 G_OBJECT_CLASS (caja_icon_container_parent_class)->finalize (object);
4470}

4475clear_size_allocation_count (gpointer data)
4476{

4478
4479 container = CAJA_ICON_CONTAINER (data);
4480
4481 container->details->size_allocation_count_id = 0;

4483

4486
4487static void
4488size_allocate (GtkWidget *widget,
4489 GtkAllocation *allocation)
4490{
4491 CajaIconContainer *container;
4492 gboolean need_layout_redone;
4493 GtkAllocation wid_allocation;
4494
4495 container = CAJA_ICON_CONTAINER (widget);
4496
4497 need_layout_redone = !container->details->has_been_allocated;
4498 gtk_widget_get_allocation (widget, &wid_allocation);
4499
4500 if (allocation->width != wid_allocation.width)
4501 {
4502 need_layout_redone = TRUE;
4503 }
4504
4505 if (allocation->height != wid_allocation.height)
4506 {
4507 need_layout_redone = TRUE;
4508 }
4509
4510 /* Under some conditions we can end up in a loop when size allocating.
4511 * This happens when the icons don't fit without a scrollbar, but fits
4512 * when a scrollbar is added (bug #129963 for details).
4513 * We keep track of this looping by increasing a counter in size_allocate
4514 * and clearing it in a high-prio idle (the only way to detect the loop is
4515 * done).
4516 * When we've done at more than two iterations (with/without scrollbar)
4517 * we terminate this looping by not redoing the layout when the width
4518 * is wider than the current one (i.e when removing the scrollbar).
4519 */
4520 if (container->details->size_allocation_count_id == 0)
4521 {
4522 container->details->size_allocation_count_id =
4523 g_idle_add_full (G_PRIORITY_HIGH,
4524 clear_size_allocation_count,
4525 container, NULL);
4526 }
4527 container->details->size_allocation_count++;
4528 if (container->details->size_allocation_count > 2 &&
4529 allocation->width >= wid_allocation.width)
4530 {
4531 need_layout_redone = FALSE;
4532 }
4533
4534 GTK_WIDGET_CLASS (caja_icon_container_parent_class)->size_allocate (widget, allocation);
4535
4536 container->details->has_been_allocated = TRUE;
4537
4538 if (need_layout_redone)
4539 {
4540 redo_layout (container);
4541 }
4542}
4543
4544static GtkSizeRequestMode
4545get_request_mode (GtkWidget *widget)
4546{
4547 /* Don't trade size at all, since we get whatever we get anyway. */
4548 return GTK_SIZE_REQUEST_CONSTANT_SIZE;
4549}
4550
4551 /* We need to implement these since the GtkScrolledWindow uses them
4552 to guess whether to show scrollbars or not, and if we don't report
4553 anything it'll tend to get it wrong causing double calls
4554 to size_allocate (at different sizes) during its size allocation. */
4555static void
4556get_prefered_width (GtkWidget *widget,
4557 gint *minimum_size,
4558 gint *natural_size)
4559{
4560 EelCanvasGroup *root;
4561 double x1, x2;
4562 int cx1, cx2;
4563 int width;
4564
4565 root = eel_canvas_root (EEL_CANVAS (widget));
4566 eel_canvas_item_get_bounds (EEL_CANVAS_ITEM (root),
4567 &x1, NULL, &x2, NULL);
4568 eel_canvas_w2c (EEL_CANVAS (widget), x1, 0, &cx1, NULL);
4569 eel_canvas_w2c (EEL_CANVAS (widget), x2, 0, &cx2, NULL);
4570
4571 width = cx2 - cx1;
4572 if (natural_size) {
4573 *natural_size = width;
4574 }
4575 if (minimum_size) {
4576 *minimum_size = width;
4577 }
4578}
4579
4580static void
4581get_prefered_height (GtkWidget *widget,
4582 gint *minimum_size,
4583 gint *natural_size)
4584{
4585 EelCanvasGroup *root;
4586 double y1, y2;
4587 int cy1, cy2;
4588 int height;
4589
4590 root = eel_canvas_root (EEL_CANVAS (widget));
4591 eel_canvas_item_get_bounds (EEL_CANVAS_ITEM (root),
4592 NULL, &y1, NULL, &y2);
4593 eel_canvas_w2c (EEL_CANVAS (widget), 0, y1, NULL, &cy1);
4594 eel_canvas_w2c (EEL_CANVAS (widget), 0, y2, NULL, &cy2);
4595
4596 height = cy2 - cy1;
4597 if (natural_size) {
4598 *natural_size = height;
4599 }
4600 if (minimum_size) {
4601 *minimum_size = height;
4602 }
4603}
4604
4605static gboolean
4606draw (GtkWidget *widget, cairo_t *cr)
4607{
4608 if (!CAJA_ICON_CONTAINER (widget)->details->is_desktop)
4609 {
4610 eel_background_draw (widget, cr);
4611 }
4612 /*If this is the desktop on wayland, we must draw it from here
4613 *Calling eel_background_draw() from caja_desktop_window_class_init()
4614 *as we do in x11 gives a black background on wayland
4615 *Wayland is always composited but never has a root window
4616 *We don't have a root window to draw on
4617 *the code used for x11 without compositing somehow fails too
4618 *But we can get caja's toplevel window from here and draw on it
4619 */
4620 if ((!(GDK_IS_X11_DISPLAY (gdk_display_get_default()))) && (CAJA_ICON_CONTAINER (widget)->details->is_desktop))
4621 {
4622 GtkWidget *toplevel = gtk_widget_get_toplevel(widget);
4623 eel_background_draw (toplevel, cr);
4624 }
4625
4626 return GTK_WIDGET_CLASS (caja_icon_container_parent_class)->draw (widget,
4627 cr);
4628}

4649 G_CALLBACK (handle_vadjustment_changed), widget);

4651}

4671static void
4672style_updated (GtkWidget *widget)
4673{
4674 CajaIconContainer *container;
4675
4676 container = CAJA_ICON_CONTAINER (widget);
4677 container->details->use_drop_shadows = container->details->drop_shadows_requested;
4678
4679 /* Don't chain up to parent, if this is a desktop container,
4680 * because that resets the background of the window.
4681 */
4682 if (!caja_icon_container_get_is_desktop (container)) {
4683 GTK_WIDGET_CLASS (caja_icon_container_parent_class)->style_updated (widget);
4684 }

4686 if (gtk_widget_get_realized (widget))

4689 caja_icon_container_request_update_all (container);
4690 }

4692
4693static gboolean
4694button_press_event (GtkWidget *widget,
4695 GdkEventButton *event)
4696{
4697 CajaIconContainer *container;
4698 gboolean selection_changed;
4699 gboolean return_value;
4700 gboolean clicked_on_icon;
4701
4702 container = CAJA_ICON_CONTAINER (widget);
4703 container->details->button_down_time = event->time;
4704
4705 /* Forget about the old keyboard selection now that we've started mousing. */
4706 clear_keyboard_focus (container);
4707 clear_keyboard_rubberband_start (container);
4708
4709 if (event->type == GDK_2BUTTON_PRESS || event->type == GDK_3BUTTON_PRESS)
4710 {
4711 /* We use our own double-click detection. */
4712 return TRUE;
4713 }
4714
4715 /* Invoke the canvas event handler and see if an item picks up the event. */
4716 clicked_on_icon = GTK_WIDGET_CLASS (caja_icon_container_parent_class)->button_press_event (widget, event);
4717
4718 /* Move focus to icon container, unless we're still renaming (to avoid exiting
4719 * renaming mode)
4720 */
4721 if (!gtk_widget_has_focus (widget) && !(is_renaming (container) || is_renaming_pending (container)))
4722 {
4723 gtk_widget_grab_focus (widget);
4724 }
4725
4726 if (clicked_on_icon)
4727 {
4728 return TRUE;
4729 }
4730
4731 if (event->button == DRAG_BUTTON &&
4732 event->type == GDK_BUTTON_PRESS)
4733 {
4734 /* Clear the last click icon for double click */
4735 container->details->double_click_icon[1] = container->details->double_click_icon[0];
4736 container->details->double_click_icon[0] = NULL;
4737 }
4738
4739 /* Button 1 does rubber banding. */
4740 if (event->button == RUBBERBAND_BUTTON)
4741 {
4742 if (! button_event_modifies_selection (event))
4743 {
4744 selection_changed = unselect_all (container);
4745 if (selection_changed)
4746 {
4747 g_signal_emit (container,
4748 signals[SELECTION_CHANGED], 0);
4749 }
4750 }
4751
4752 start_rubberbanding (container, event);
4753 return TRUE;
4754 }
4755
4756 /* Prevent multi-button weirdness such as bug 6181 */
4757 if (container->details->rubberband_info.active)
4758 {
4759 return TRUE;
4760 }
4761
4762 /* Button 2 may be passed to the window manager. */
4763 if (event->button == MIDDLE_BUTTON)
4764 {
4765 selection_changed = unselect_all (container);
4766 if (selection_changed)
4767 {
4768 g_signal_emit (container, signals[SELECTION_CHANGED], 0);
4769 }
4770 g_signal_emit (widget, signals[MIDDLE_CLICK], 0, event);
4771 return TRUE;
4772 }
4773
4774 /* Button 3 does a contextual menu. */
4775 if (event->button == CONTEXTUAL_MENU_BUTTON)
4776 {
4777 end_renaming_mode (container, TRUE);
4778 selection_changed = unselect_all (container);
4779 if (selection_changed)
4780 {
4781 g_signal_emit (container, signals[SELECTION_CHANGED], 0);
4782 }
4783 g_signal_emit (widget, signals[CONTEXT_CLICK_BACKGROUND], 0, event);
4784 return TRUE;
4785 }
4786
4787 /* Otherwise, we emit a button_press message. */
4788 g_signal_emit (widget,
4789 signals[BUTTON_PRESS], 0, event,
4790 &return_value);
4791 return return_value;
4792}
4793
4794static void
4795caja_icon_container_did_not_drag (CajaIconContainer *container,
4796 GdkEventButton *event)
4797{
4798 CajaIconContainerDetails *details;
4799 gboolean selection_changed;
4800 static gint64 last_click_time = 0;
4801 static gint click_count = 0;
4802 gint double_click_time;
4803 gint64 current_time;
4804
4805 details = container->details;
4806
4807 if (details->icon_selected_on_button_down &&
4808 ((event->state & GDK_CONTROL_MASK) != 0 ||
4809 (event->state & GDK_SHIFT_MASK) == 0))
4810 {
4811 if (button_event_modifies_selection (event))
4812 {
4813 details->range_selection_base_icon = NULL;
4814 icon_toggle_selected (container, details->drag_icon);
4815 g_signal_emit (container,
4816 signals[SELECTION_CHANGED], 0);
4817 }
4818 else
4819 {
4820 details->range_selection_base_icon = details->drag_icon;
4821 selection_changed = select_one_unselect_others
4822 (container, details->drag_icon);
4823
4824 if (selection_changed)
4825 {
4826 g_signal_emit (container,
4827 signals[SELECTION_CHANGED], 0);
4828 }
4829 }
4830 }
4831
4832 if (details->drag_icon != NULL &&
4833 (details->single_click_mode ||
4834 event->button == MIDDLE_BUTTON))
4835 {
4836 /* Determine click count */
4837 g_object_get (G_OBJECT (gtk_widget_get_settings (GTK_WIDGET (container))),
4838 "gtk-double-click-time", &double_click_time,
4839 NULL);
4840 current_time = g_get_monotonic_time ();
4841 if (current_time - last_click_time < double_click_time * 1000)
4842 {
4843 click_count++;
4844 }
4845 else
4846 {
4847 click_count = 0;
4848 }
4849
4850 /* Stash time for next compare */
4851 last_click_time = current_time;
4852
4853 /* If single-click mode, activate the selected icons, unless modifying
4854 * the selection or pressing for a very long time, or double clicking.
4855 */
4856
4857 if (click_count == 0 &&
4858 event->time - details->button_down_time < MAX_CLICK_TIME &&
4859 ! button_event_modifies_selection (event))
4860 {
4861
4862 /* It's a tricky UI issue whether this should activate
4863 * just the clicked item (as if it were a link), or all
4864 * the selected items (as if you were issuing an "activate
4865 * selection" command). For now, we're trying the activate
4866 * entire selection version to see how it feels. Note that
4867 * CajaList goes the other way because its "links" seem
4868 * much more link-like.
4869 */
4870 if (event->button == MIDDLE_BUTTON)
4871 {
4872 activate_selected_items_alternate (container, NULL);
4873 }
4874 else
4875 {
4876 activate_selected_items (container);
4877 }
4878 }
4879 }
4880}
4881
4882static gboolean
4883clicked_within_double_click_interval (CajaIconContainer *container)
4884{
4885 static gint64 last_click_time = 0;
4886 static gint click_count = 0;
4887 gint double_click_time;
4888 gint64 current_time;
4889
4890 /* Determine click count */
4891 g_object_get (G_OBJECT (gtk_widget_get_settings (GTK_WIDGET (container))),
4892 "gtk-double-click-time", &double_click_time,
4893 NULL);
4894 current_time = g_get_monotonic_time ();
4895 if (current_time - last_click_time < double_click_time * 1000)
4896 {
4897 click_count++;
4898 }
4899 else
4900 {
4901 click_count = 0;
4902 }
4903
4904 /* Stash time for next compare */
4905 last_click_time = current_time;
4906
4907 /* Only allow double click */
4908 if (click_count == 1) {
4909 click_count = 0;
4910 return TRUE;
4911 } else {
4912 return FALSE;
4913 }
4914}
4915
4916static void
4917clear_drag_state (CajaIconContainer *container)
4918{
4919 container->details->drag_icon = NULL;
4920 container->details->drag_state = DRAG_STATE_INITIAL;
4921}
4922
4923static gboolean
4924start_stretching (CajaIconContainer *container,
4925 GdkEvent *event)
4926{
4927 CajaIconContainerDetails *details;
4928 CajaIcon *icon;
4929 EelDPoint world_point;
4930 GtkWidget *toplevel;
4931 GdkDisplay *display;
4932 GtkCornerType corner;
4933 GdkCursor *cursor;
4934
4935 details = container->details;
4936 icon = details->stretch_icon;
4937 display = gtk_widget_get_display (GTK_WIDGET (container));
4938
4939 /* Check if we hit the stretch handles. */
4940 world_point.x = details->drag_x;
4941 world_point.y = details->drag_y;
4942 if (!caja_icon_canvas_item_hit_test_stretch_handles (icon->item, world_point, &corner))
4943 {
4944 return FALSE;
4945 }
4946
4947 switch (corner)
4948 {
4949 case GTK_CORNER_TOP_LEFT:
4950 cursor = gdk_cursor_new_for_display (display, GDK_TOP_LEFT_CORNER);
4951 break;
4952 case GTK_CORNER_BOTTOM_LEFT:
4953 cursor = gdk_cursor_new_for_display (display, GDK_BOTTOM_LEFT_CORNER);
4954 break;
4955 case GTK_CORNER_TOP_RIGHT:
4956 cursor = gdk_cursor_new_for_display (display, GDK_TOP_RIGHT_CORNER);
4957 break;
4958 case GTK_CORNER_BOTTOM_RIGHT:
4959 cursor = gdk_cursor_new_for_display (display, GDK_BOTTOM_RIGHT_CORNER);
4960 break;
4961 default:
4962 cursor = NULL;
4963 break;
4964 }
4965 /* Set up the dragging. */
4966 details->drag_state = DRAG_STATE_STRETCH;
4967 eel_canvas_w2c (EEL_CANVAS (container),
4968 details->drag_x,
4969 details->drag_y,
4970 &details->stretch_start.pointer_x,
4971 &details->stretch_start.pointer_y);
4972 eel_canvas_w2c (EEL_CANVAS (container),
4973 icon->x, icon->y,
4974 &details->stretch_start.icon_x,
4975 &details->stretch_start.icon_y);
4976 icon_get_size (container, icon,
4977 &details->stretch_start.icon_size);
4978
4979 eel_canvas_item_grab (EEL_CANVAS_ITEM (icon->item),
4980 (GDK_POINTER_MOTION_MASK
4981 | GDK_BUTTON_RELEASE_MASK),
4982 cursor,
4983 event);
4984
4985 if (cursor)
4986 g_object_unref (cursor);
4987
4988 /* Ensure the window itself is focused.. */
4989 toplevel = gtk_widget_get_toplevel (GTK_WIDGET (container));
4990 if (toplevel != NULL && gtk_widget_get_realized (toplevel))
4991 {
4992 gdk_window_focus (gtk_widget_get_window (toplevel), GDK_CURRENT_TIME);
4993 }
4994
4995 return TRUE;
4996}
4997
4998static gboolean
4999update_stretch_at_idle (CajaIconContainer *container)
5000{
5001 CajaIconContainerDetails *details;
5002 CajaIcon *icon;
5003 double world_x, world_y;
5004 StretchState stretch_state;
5005
5006 details = container->details;
5007 icon = details->stretch_icon;
5008
5009 if (icon == NULL)
5010 {
5011 container->details->stretch_idle_id = 0;
5012 return FALSE;
5013 }
5014
5015 eel_canvas_w2c (EEL_CANVAS (container),
5016 details->world_x, details->world_y,
5017 &stretch_state.pointer_x, &stretch_state.pointer_y);
5018
5019 compute_stretch (&details->stretch_start,
5020 &stretch_state);
5021
5022 eel_canvas_c2w (EEL_CANVAS (container),
5023 stretch_state.icon_x, stretch_state.icon_y,
5024 &world_x, &world_y);
5025
5026 icon_set_position (icon, world_x, world_y);
5027 icon_set_size (container, icon, stretch_state.icon_size, FALSE, FALSE);
5028
5029 container->details->stretch_idle_id = 0;
5030
5031 return FALSE;
5032}
5033
5034static void
5035continue_stretching (CajaIconContainer *container,
5036 double world_x, double world_y)
5037{
5038
5039 g_return_if_fail (CAJA_IS_ICON_CONTAINER (container));
5040
5041 container->details->world_x = world_x;
5042 container->details->world_y = world_y;
5043
5044 if (container->details->stretch_idle_id == 0)
5045 {
5046 container->details->stretch_idle_id = g_idle_add ((GSourceFunc) update_stretch_at_idle, container);
5047 }
5048}
5049
5050static gboolean
5051keyboard_stretching (CajaIconContainer *container,
5052 GdkEventKey *event)
5053{
5054 CajaIcon *icon;
5055 guint size;
5056
5057 icon = container->details->stretch_icon;
5058
5059 if (icon == NULL || !icon->is_selected)
5060 {
5061 return FALSE;
5062 }
5063
5064 icon_get_size (container, icon, &size);
5065
5066 switch (event->keyval)
5067 {
5068 case GDK_KEY_equal:
5069 case GDK_KEY_plus:
5070 case GDK_KEY_KP_Add:
5071 icon_set_size (container, icon, size + 5, FALSE, FALSE);
5072 break;
5073 case GDK_KEY_minus:
5074 case GDK_KEY_KP_Subtract:
5075 icon_set_size (container, icon, size - 5, FALSE, FALSE);
5076 break;
5077 case GDK_KEY_0:
5078 case GDK_KEY_KP_0:
5079 caja_icon_container_move_icon (container, icon,
5080 icon->x, icon->y,
5081 1.0,
5082 FALSE, TRUE, TRUE);
5083 break;
5084 }
5085
5086 return TRUE;
5087}
5088
5089static void
5090ungrab_stretch_icon (CajaIconContainer *container)
5091{
5092 eel_canvas_item_ungrab (EEL_CANVAS_ITEM (container->details->stretch_icon->item));
5093}
5094
5095static void
5096end_stretching (CajaIconContainer *container,
5097 double world_x, double world_y)
5098{
5099 CajaIconPosition position;
5100 CajaIcon *icon;
5101
5102 continue_stretching (container, world_x, world_y);
5103 ungrab_stretch_icon (container);
5104
5105 /* now that we're done stretching, update the icon's position */
5106
5107 icon = container->details->drag_icon;
5108 if (caja_icon_container_is_layout_rtl (container))
5109 {
5110 position.x = icon->saved_ltr_x = get_mirror_x_position (container, icon, icon->x);
5111 }
5112 else
5113 {
5114 position.x = icon->x;
5115 }
5116 position.y = icon->y;
5117 position.scale = icon->scale;
5118 g_signal_emit (container,
5119 signals[ICON_POSITION_CHANGED], 0,
5120 icon->data, &position);
5121
5122 clear_drag_state (container);
5123 redo_layout (container);
5124}
5125
5126static gboolean
5127undo_stretching (CajaIconContainer *container)
5128{
5129 CajaIcon *stretched_icon;
5130
5131 stretched_icon = container->details->stretch_icon;
5132
5133 if (stretched_icon == NULL)
5134 {
5135 return FALSE;
5136 }
5137
5138 if (container->details->drag_state == DRAG_STATE_STRETCH)
5139 {
5140 ungrab_stretch_icon (container);
5141 clear_drag_state (container);
5142 }
5143 caja_icon_canvas_item_set_show_stretch_handles
5144 (stretched_icon->item, FALSE);
5145
5146 icon_set_position (stretched_icon,
5147 container->details->stretch_initial_x,
5148 container->details->stretch_initial_y);
5149 icon_set_size (container,
5150 stretched_icon,
5151 container->details->stretch_initial_size,
5152 TRUE,
5153 TRUE);
5154
5155 container->details->stretch_icon = NULL;
5156 emit_stretch_ended (container, stretched_icon);
5157 redo_layout (container);
5158
5159 return TRUE;
5160}
5161
5162static gboolean
5163button_release_event (GtkWidget *widget,
5164 GdkEventButton *event)
5165{
5166 CajaIconContainer *container;
5167 CajaIconContainerDetails *details;
5168 double world_x, world_y;
5169
5170 container = CAJA_ICON_CONTAINER (widget);
5171 details = container->details;
5172
5173 if (event->button == RUBBERBAND_BUTTON && details->rubberband_info.active)
5174 {
5175 stop_rubberbanding (container);
5176 return TRUE;
5177 }
5178
5179 if (event->button == details->drag_button)
5180 {
5181 details->drag_button = 0;
5182
5183 switch (details->drag_state)
5184 {
5185 case DRAG_STATE_MOVE_OR_COPY:
5186 if (!details->drag_started)
5187 {
5188 caja_icon_container_did_not_drag (container, event);
5189 }
5190 else
5191 {
5192 caja_icon_dnd_end_drag (container);
5193 caja_debug_log (FALSE, CAJA_DEBUG_LOG_DOMAIN_USER,
5194 "end drag from icon container");
5195 }
5196 break;
5197 case DRAG_STATE_STRETCH:
5198 eel_canvas_window_to_world
5199 (EEL_CANVAS (container), event->x, event->y, &world_x, &world_y);
5200 end_stretching (container, world_x, world_y);
5201 break;
5202 default:
5203 break;
5204 }
5205
5206 clear_drag_state (container);
5207 return TRUE;
5208 }
5209
5210 return GTK_WIDGET_CLASS (caja_icon_container_parent_class)->button_release_event (widget, event);
5211}
5212
5213static int
5214motion_notify_event (GtkWidget *widget,
5215 GdkEventMotion *event)
5216{
5217 CajaIconContainer *container;
5218 CajaIconContainerDetails *details;
5219 double world_x, world_y;
5220 int canvas_x, canvas_y;
5221 GdkDragAction actions;
5222
5223 container = CAJA_ICON_CONTAINER (widget);
5224 details = container->details;
5225
5226 if (details->drag_button != 0)
5227 {
5228 switch (details->drag_state)
5229 {
5230 case DRAG_STATE_MOVE_OR_COPY:
5231 if (details->drag_started)
5232 {
5233 break;
5234 }
5235
5236 eel_canvas_window_to_world
5237 (EEL_CANVAS (container), event->x, event->y, &world_x, &world_y);
5238
5239 if (gtk_drag_check_threshold (widget,
5240 details->drag_x,
5241 details->drag_y,
5242 world_x,
5243 world_y))
5244 {
5245 details->drag_started = TRUE;
5246 details->drag_state = DRAG_STATE_MOVE_OR_COPY;
5247
5248 end_renaming_mode (container, TRUE);
5249
5250 eel_canvas_w2c (EEL_CANVAS (container),
5251 details->drag_x,
5252 details->drag_y,
5253 &canvas_x,
5254 &canvas_y);
5255
5256 actions = GDK_ACTION_COPY
5257 | GDK_ACTION_LINK
5258 | GDK_ACTION_ASK;
5259
5260 if (container->details->drag_allow_moves)
5261 {
5262 actions |= GDK_ACTION_MOVE;
5263 }
5264
5265 caja_icon_dnd_begin_drag (container,
5266 actions,
5267 details->drag_button,
5268 event,
5269 canvas_x,
5270 canvas_y);
5271 caja_debug_log (FALSE, CAJA_DEBUG_LOG_DOMAIN_USER,
5272 "begin drag from icon container");
5273 }
5274 break;
5275 case DRAG_STATE_STRETCH:
5276 eel_canvas_window_to_world
5277 (EEL_CANVAS (container), event->x, event->y, &world_x, &world_y);
5278 continue_stretching (container, world_x, world_y);
5279 break;
5280 default:
5281 break;
5282 }
5283 }
5284
5285 return GTK_WIDGET_CLASS (caja_icon_container_parent_class)->motion_notify_event (widget, event);
5286}
5287
5288static void
5289caja_icon_container_search_position_func (CajaIconContainer *container,
5290 GtkWidget *search_dialog)
5291{
5292 gint x, y;
5293 gint cont_x, cont_y;
5294 gint cont_width, cont_height;
5295 GdkWindow *cont_window;
5296 GdkScreen *screen;
5297 GtkRequisition requisition;
5298 GdkMonitor *monitor_num;
5299 GdkRectangle monitor;
5300 GdkRectangle workarea = {0};
5301
5302 cont_window = gtk_widget_get_window (GTK_WIDGET (container));
5303 screen = gdk_window_get_screen (cont_window);
5304
5305 monitor_num = gdk_display_get_monitor_at_window (gdk_display_get_default(), cont_window);
5306 gdk_monitor_get_workarea(monitor_num, &workarea);
5307
5308 monitor_num = gdk_display_get_monitor_at_window (gdk_screen_get_display (screen),
5309 cont_window);
5310 gdk_monitor_get_geometry (monitor_num, &monitor);
5311
5312 gtk_widget_realize (search_dialog);
5313
5314 gdk_window_get_origin (cont_window, &cont_x, &cont_y);
5315
5316 cont_width = gdk_window_get_width (cont_window);
5317 cont_height = gdk_window_get_height (cont_window);
5318
5319 gtk_widget_get_preferred_size (search_dialog, &requisition, NULL);
5320
5321 if (cont_x + cont_width - requisition.width > workarea.width)
5322 {
5323 x = workarea.width - requisition.width;
5324 }
5325 else if (cont_x + cont_width - requisition.width < 0)
5326 {
5327 x = 0;
5328 }
5329 else
5330 {
5331 x = cont_x + cont_width - requisition.width;
5332 }
5333
5334 if (cont_y + cont_height > workarea.height)
5335 {
5336 y = workarea.height - requisition.height;
5337 }
5338 else if (cont_y + cont_height < 0) /* isn't really possible ... */
5339 {
5340 y = 0;
5341 }
5342 else
5343 {
5344 y = cont_y + cont_height;
5345 }
5346
5347 gtk_window_move (GTK_WINDOW (search_dialog), x, y);
5348}

5385/* Cut and paste from gtkwindow.c */
5386static void
5387send_focus_change (GtkWidget *widget, gboolean in)
5388{
5389 GdkEvent *fevent;
5390
5391 fevent = gdk_event_new (GDK_FOCUS_CHANGE);
5392
5393 g_object_ref (widget);
5394 ((GdkEventFocus *) fevent)->in = in;
5395
5396 gtk_widget_send_focus_change (widget, fevent);
5397
5398 fevent->focus_change.type = GDK_FOCUS_CHANGE;
5399 fevent->focus_change.window = g_object_ref (gtk_widget_get_window (widget));
5400 fevent->focus_change.in = in;
5401
5402 gtk_widget_event (widget, fevent);
5403
5404 g_object_notify (G_OBJECT (widget), "has-focus");
5405
5406 g_object_unref (widget);
5407 gdk_event_free (fevent);
5408}

5410static void
5411caja_icon_container_search_dialog_hide (GtkWidget *search_dialog,
5412 CajaIconContainer *container)
5413{
5414 if (container->details->disable_popdown)
5415 {
5416 return;
5417 }
5418

5420 {
5421 g_signal_handler_disconnect (container->details->search_entry,
5422 container->details->search_entry_changed_id);
5423 container->details->search_entry_changed_id = 0;
5424 }
5425 if (container->details->typeselect_flush_timeout)
5426 {
5427 g_source_remove (container->details->typeselect_flush_timeout);
5428 container->details->typeselect_flush_timeout = 0;
5429 }
5430
5431 /* send focus-in event */
5432 send_focus_change (GTK_WIDGET (container->details->search_entry), FALSE);
5433 gtk_widget_hide (search_dialog);
5434 gtk_entry_set_text (GTK_ENTRY (container->details->search_entry), "");
5435}

5517
5518static gboolean
5519caja_icon_container_search_iter (CajaIconContainer *container,
5520 const char *key, gint n)
5521{
5522 GList *p;
5523 CajaIcon *icon;
5524 char *name;
5525 int count;
5526 char *normalized_key, *case_normalized_key;
5527 char *normalized_name, *case_normalized_name;
5528
5529 g_assert (key != NULL);
5530 g_assert (n >= 1);
5531
5532 normalized_key = g_utf8_normalize (key, -1, G_NORMALIZE_ALL);
5533 if (!normalized_key)
5534 {
5535 return FALSE;
5536 }
5537 case_normalized_key = g_utf8_casefold (normalized_key, -1);
5538 g_free (normalized_key);
5539 if (!case_normalized_key)
5540 {
5541 return FALSE;
5542 }
5543
5544 icon = NULL;
5545 name = NULL;
5546 count = 0;
5547 for (p = container->details->icons; p != NULL && count != n; p = p->next)
5548 {
5549 icon = p->data;
5550 caja_icon_container_get_icon_text (container, icon->data, &name,
5551 NULL, TRUE);
5552
5553 /* This can happen if a key event is handled really early while
5554 * loading the icon container, before the items have all been
5555 * updated once.
5556 */
5557 if (!name)
5558 {
5559 continue;
5560 }
5561
5562 normalized_name = g_utf8_normalize (name, -1, G_NORMALIZE_ALL);
5563 if (!normalized_name)
5564 {
5565 continue;
5566 }
5567 case_normalized_name = g_utf8_casefold (normalized_name, -1);
5568 g_free (normalized_name);
5569 if (!case_normalized_name)
5570 {
5571 continue;
5572 }
5573
5574 if (strncmp (case_normalized_key, case_normalized_name,
5575 strlen (case_normalized_key)) == 0)
5576 {
5577 count++;
5578 }
5579
5580 g_free (case_normalized_name);
5581 g_free (name);
5582 name = NULL;
5583 }
5584
5585 g_free (case_normalized_key);
5586
5587 if (count == n)
5588 {
5589 if (select_one_unselect_others (container, icon))
5590 {
5591 g_signal_emit (container, signals[SELECTION_CHANGED], 0);
5592 }
5593 schedule_keyboard_icon_reveal (container, icon);
5594
5595 return TRUE;
5596 }
5597
5598 return FALSE;
5599}
5600
5601static void
5602caja_icon_container_search_move (GtkWidget *window,
5603 CajaIconContainer *container,
5604 gboolean up)
5605{
5606 gboolean ret;
5607 gint len;
5608 const gchar *text;
5609
5610 text = gtk_entry_get_text (GTK_ENTRY (container->details->search_entry));
5611
5612 g_assert (text != NULL);
5613
5614 if (container->details->selected_iter == 0)
5615 {
5616 return;
5617 }
5618
5619 if (up && container->details->selected_iter == 1)
5620 {
5621 return;
5622 }
5623
5624 len = strlen (text);
5625
5626 if (len < 1)
5627 {
5628 return;
5629 }
5630
5631 /* search */
5632 unselect_all (container);
5633
5634 ret = caja_icon_container_search_iter (container, text,
5635 up?((container->details->selected_iter) - 1):((container->details->selected_iter + 1)));
5636
5637 if (ret)
5638 {
5639 /* found */
5640 container->details->selected_iter += up?(-1):(1);
5641 }
5642 else
5643 {
5644 /* return to old iter */
5645 caja_icon_container_search_iter (container, text,
5646 container->details->selected_iter);
5647 }
5648}
5649
5650static gboolean
5651caja_icon_container_search_scroll_event (GtkWidget *widget,
5652 GdkEventScroll *event,
5653 CajaIconContainer *container)
5654{
5655 gboolean retval = FALSE;
5656
5657 if (event->direction == GDK_SCROLL_UP)
5658 {
5659 caja_icon_container_search_move (widget, container, TRUE);
5660 retval = TRUE;
5661 }
5662 else if (event->direction == GDK_SCROLL_DOWN)
5663 {
5664 caja_icon_container_search_move (widget, container, FALSE);
5665 retval = TRUE;
5666 }
5667
5668 /* renew the flush timeout */
5669 if (retval && container->details->typeselect_flush_timeout)
5670 {
5671 g_source_remove (container->details->typeselect_flush_timeout);
5672 container->details->typeselect_flush_timeout =
5673 g_timeout_add_seconds (CAJA_ICON_CONTAINER_SEARCH_DIALOG_TIMEOUT,
5674 (GSourceFunc) caja_icon_container_search_entry_flush_timeout,
5675 container);
5676 }
5677
5678 return retval;
5679}
5680
5681static gboolean
5682caja_icon_container_search_key_press_event (GtkWidget *widget,
5683 GdkEventKey *event,
5684 CajaIconContainer *container)
5685{
5686 gboolean retval = FALSE;
5687
5688 g_assert (GTK_IS_WIDGET (widget));
5689 g_assert (CAJA_IS_ICON_CONTAINER (container));
5690
5691 /* close window and cancel the search */
5692 if (event->keyval == GDK_KEY_Escape || event->keyval == GDK_KEY_Tab)
5693 {
5694 caja_icon_container_search_dialog_hide (widget, container);
5695 return TRUE;
5696 }
5697
5698 /* close window and activate alternate */
5699 if (event->keyval == GDK_KEY_Return && event->state & GDK_SHIFT_MASK)
5700 {
5701 caja_icon_container_search_dialog_hide (widget,
5702 container);
5703
5704 activate_selected_items_alternate (container, NULL);
5705 return TRUE;
5706 }
5707
5708 /* select previous matching iter */
5709 if (event->keyval == GDK_KEY_Up || event->keyval == GDK_KEY_KP_Up)
5710 {
5711 caja_icon_container_search_move (widget, container, TRUE);
5712 retval = TRUE;
5713 }
5714
5715 if (((event->state & (GDK_CONTROL_MASK | GDK_SHIFT_MASK)) == (GDK_CONTROL_MASK | GDK_SHIFT_MASK))
5716 && (event->keyval == GDK_KEY_g || event->keyval == GDK_KEY_G))
5717 {
5718 caja_icon_container_search_move (widget, container, TRUE);
5719 retval = TRUE;
5720 }
5721
5722 /* select next matching iter */
5723 if (event->keyval == GDK_KEY_Down || event->keyval == GDK_KEY_KP_Down)
5724 {
5725 caja_icon_container_search_move (widget, container, FALSE);
5726 retval = TRUE;
5727 }
5728
5729 if (((event->state & (GDK_CONTROL_MASK | GDK_SHIFT_MASK)) == GDK_CONTROL_MASK)
5730 && (event->keyval == GDK_KEY_g || event->keyval == GDK_KEY_G))
5731 {
5732 caja_icon_container_search_move (widget, container, FALSE);
5733 retval = TRUE;
5734 }
5735
5736 /* renew the flush timeout */
5737 if (retval && container->details->typeselect_flush_timeout)
5738 {
5739 g_source_remove (container->details->typeselect_flush_timeout);
5740 container->details->typeselect_flush_timeout =
5741 g_timeout_add_seconds (CAJA_ICON_CONTAINER_SEARCH_DIALOG_TIMEOUT,
5742 (GSourceFunc) caja_icon_container_search_entry_flush_timeout,
5743 container);
5744 }
5745
5746 return retval;
5747}
5748
5749static void
5750caja_icon_container_search_init (GtkWidget *entry,
5751 CajaIconContainer *container)
5752{
5753 gint ret;
5754 gint len;
5755 const gchar *text;
5756
5757 g_assert (GTK_IS_ENTRY (entry));
5758 g_assert (CAJA_IS_ICON_CONTAINER (container));
5759
5760 text = gtk_entry_get_text (GTK_ENTRY (entry));
5761 len = strlen (text);
5762
5763 /* search */
5764 unselect_all (container);
5765 if (container->details->typeselect_flush_timeout)
5766 {
5767 g_source_remove (container->details->typeselect_flush_timeout);
5768 container->details->typeselect_flush_timeout =
5769 g_timeout_add_seconds (CAJA_ICON_CONTAINER_SEARCH_DIALOG_TIMEOUT,
5770 (GSourceFunc) caja_icon_container_search_entry_flush_timeout,
5771 container);
5772 }
5773
5774 if (len < 1)
5775 {
5776 return;
5777 }
5778
5779 ret = caja_icon_container_search_iter (container, text, 1);
5780
5781 if (ret)
5782 {
5783 container->details->selected_iter = 1;
5784 }
5785}
5786
5787static void
5788caja_icon_container_ensure_interactive_directory (CajaIconContainer *container)
5789{
5790 GtkWidget *frame, *vbox, *toplevel;
5791
5792 if (container->details->search_window != NULL)
5793 {
5794 return;
5795 }
5796
5797 container->details->search_window = gtk_window_new (GTK_WINDOW_POPUP);
5798 toplevel = gtk_widget_get_toplevel (GTK_WIDGET (container));
5799
5800 gtk_window_set_modal (GTK_WINDOW (container->details->search_window), TRUE);
5801 gtk_window_set_decorated (GTK_WINDOW (container->details->search_window), FALSE);
5802 gtk_window_set_transient_for (GTK_WINDOW (container->details->search_window),
5803 GTK_WINDOW (toplevel));
5804
5805 gtk_window_set_destroy_with_parent (GTK_WINDOW (container->details->search_window), TRUE);
5806 gtk_window_set_type_hint (GTK_WINDOW (container->details->search_window),
5807 GDK_WINDOW_TYPE_HINT_COMBO);
5808
5809 g_signal_connect (container->details->search_window, "delete_event",
5810 G_CALLBACK (caja_icon_container_search_delete_event),
5811 container);
5812 g_signal_connect (container->details->search_window, "key_press_event",
5813 G_CALLBACK (caja_icon_container_search_key_press_event),
5814 container);
5815 g_signal_connect (container->details->search_window, "button_press_event",
5816 G_CALLBACK (caja_icon_container_search_button_press_event),
5817 container);
5818 g_signal_connect (container->details->search_window, "scroll_event",
5819 G_CALLBACK (caja_icon_container_search_scroll_event),
5820 container);
5821
5822 frame = gtk_frame_new (NULL);
5823 gtk_frame_set_shadow_type (GTK_FRAME (frame), GTK_SHADOW_ETCHED_IN);
5824 gtk_widget_show (frame);
5825 gtk_container_add (GTK_CONTAINER (container->details->search_window), frame);
5826
5827 vbox = gtk_box_new (GTK_ORIENTATION_VERTICAL, 0);
5828 gtk_widget_show (vbox);
5829 gtk_container_add (GTK_CONTAINER (frame), vbox);
5830 gtk_container_set_border_width (GTK_CONTAINER (vbox), 3);
5831
5832 /* add entry */
5833 container->details->search_entry = gtk_entry_new ();
5834 gtk_widget_show (container->details->search_entry);
5835 g_signal_connect (container->details->search_entry, "populate_popup",
5836 G_CALLBACK (caja_icon_container_search_disable_popdown),
5837 container);
5838 g_signal_connect (container->details->search_entry, "activate",
5839 G_CALLBACK (caja_icon_container_search_activate),
5840 container);
5841 g_signal_connect (container->details->search_entry,
5842 "preedit-changed",
5843 G_CALLBACK (caja_icon_container_search_preedit_changed),
5844 container);
5845 gtk_container_add (GTK_CONTAINER (vbox), container->details->search_entry);
5846
5847 gtk_widget_realize (container->details->search_entry);
5848}
5849
5850/* Pops up the interactive search entry. If keybinding is TRUE then the user
5851 * started this by typing the start_interactive_search keybinding. Otherwise, it came from
5852 */
5853static gboolean
5854caja_icon_container_real_start_interactive_search (CajaIconContainer *container,
5855 gboolean keybinding)
5856{
5857 /* We only start interactive search if we have focus. If one of our
5858 * children have focus, we don't want to start the search.
5859 */
5860 GtkWidgetClass *entry_parent_class;
5861
5862 if (container->details->search_window != NULL &&
5863 gtk_widget_get_visible (container->details->search_window))
5864 {
5865 return TRUE;
5866 }
5867
5868 if (!gtk_widget_has_focus (GTK_WIDGET (container)))
5869 {
5870 return FALSE;
5871 }
5872
5873 caja_icon_container_ensure_interactive_directory (container);
5874
5875 if (keybinding)
5876 {
5877 gtk_entry_set_text (GTK_ENTRY (container->details->search_entry), "");
5878 }
5879
5880 /* done, show it */
5881 caja_icon_container_search_position_func (container, container->details->search_window);
5882 gtk_widget_show (container->details->search_window);
5883 if (container->details->search_entry_changed_id == 0)
5884 {
5885 container->details->search_entry_changed_id =
5886 g_signal_connect (container->details->search_entry, "changed",
5887 G_CALLBACK (caja_icon_container_search_init),
5888 container);
5889 }
5890
5891 container->details->typeselect_flush_timeout =
5892 g_timeout_add_seconds (CAJA_ICON_CONTAINER_SEARCH_DIALOG_TIMEOUT,
5893 (GSourceFunc) caja_icon_container_search_entry_flush_timeout,
5894 container);
5895
5896 /* Grab focus will select all the text. We don't want that to happen, so we
5897 * call the parent instance and bypass the selection change. This is probably
5898 * really non-kosher. */
5899 entry_parent_class = g_type_class_peek_parent (GTK_ENTRY_GET_CLASS (container->details->search_entry));
5900 (entry_parent_class->grab_focus) (container->details->search_entry);
5901
5902 /* send focus-in event */
5903 send_focus_change (container->details->search_entry, TRUE);
5904
5905 /* search first matching iter */
5906 caja_icon_container_search_init (container->details->search_entry, container);
5907
5908 return TRUE;
5909}
5910
5911static gboolean
5912caja_icon_container_start_interactive_search (CajaIconContainer *container)
5913{
5914 return caja_icon_container_real_start_interactive_search (container, TRUE);
5915}
5916
5917static gboolean
5918handle_popups (CajaIconContainer *container,
5919 GdkEventKey *event,
5920 const char *signal)
5921{
5922 GdkEventButton button_event = { 0 };
5923
5924 g_signal_emit_by_name (container, signal, &button_event);
5925
5926 return TRUE;
5927}
5928
5929static int
5930key_press_event (GtkWidget *widget,
5931 GdkEventKey *event)
5932{
5933 CajaIconContainer *container;
5934 gboolean handled;
5935
5936 container = CAJA_ICON_CONTAINER (widget);
5937 handled = FALSE;
5938
5939 if (is_renaming (container) || is_renaming_pending (container))
5940 {
5941 switch (event->keyval)
5942 {
5943 case GDK_KEY_Return:
5944 case GDK_KEY_KP_Enter:
5945 end_renaming_mode (container, TRUE);
5946 handled = TRUE;
5947 break;
5948 case GDK_KEY_Escape:
5949 end_renaming_mode (container, FALSE);
5950 handled = TRUE;
5951 break;
5952 default:
5953 break;
5954 }
5955 }
5956 else
5957 {
5958 switch (event->keyval)
5959 {
5960 case GDK_KEY_Home:
5961 case GDK_KEY_KP_Home:
5962 keyboard_home (container, event);
5963 handled = TRUE;
5964 break;
5965 case GDK_KEY_End:
5966 case GDK_KEY_KP_End:
5967 keyboard_end (container, event);
5968 handled = TRUE;
5969 break;
5970 case GDK_KEY_Left:
5971 case GDK_KEY_KP_Left:
5972 /* Don't eat Alt-Left, as that is used for history browsing */
5973 if ((event->state & GDK_MOD1_MASK) == 0)
5974 {
5975 keyboard_left (container, event);
5976 handled = TRUE;
5977 }
5978 break;
5979 case GDK_KEY_Up:
5980 case GDK_KEY_KP_Up:
5981 /* Don't eat Alt-Up, as that is used for alt-shift-Up */
5982 if ((event->state & GDK_MOD1_MASK) == 0)
5983 {
5984 keyboard_up (container, event);
5985 handled = TRUE;
5986 }
5987 break;
5988 case GDK_KEY_Right:
5989 case GDK_KEY_KP_Right:
5990 /* Don't eat Alt-Right, as that is used for history browsing */
5991 if ((event->state & GDK_MOD1_MASK) == 0)
5992 {
5993 keyboard_right (container, event);
5994 handled = TRUE;
5995 }
5996 break;
5997 case GDK_KEY_Down:
5998 case GDK_KEY_KP_Down:
5999 /* Don't eat Alt-Down, as that is used for Open */
6000 if ((event->state & GDK_MOD1_MASK) == 0)
6001 {
6002 keyboard_down (container, event);
6003 handled = TRUE;
6004 }
6005 break;
6006 case GDK_KEY_space:
6007 keyboard_space (container, event);
6008 handled = TRUE;
6009 break;
6010#ifndef TAB_NAVIGATION_DISABLED
6011 case GDK_KEY_Tab:
6012 case GDK_KEY_ISO_Left_Tab:
6013 select_previous_or_next_icon (container,
6014 (event->state & GDK_SHIFT_MASK) == 0, event);
6015 handled = TRUE;
6016 break;
6017#endif
6018 case GDK_KEY_Return:
6019 case GDK_KEY_KP_Enter:
6020 if ((event->state & GDK_SHIFT_MASK) != 0)
6021 {
6022 activate_selected_items_alternate (container, NULL);
6023 }
6024 else
6025 {
6026 activate_selected_items (container);
6027 }
6028
6029 handled = TRUE;
6030 break;
6031 case GDK_KEY_Escape:
6032 handled = undo_stretching (container);
6033 break;
6034 case GDK_KEY_plus:
6035 case GDK_KEY_minus:
6036 case GDK_KEY_equal:
6037 case GDK_KEY_KP_Add:
6038 case GDK_KEY_KP_Subtract:
6039 case GDK_KEY_0:
6040 case GDK_KEY_KP_0:
6041 if (event->state & GDK_CONTROL_MASK)
6042 {
6043 handled = keyboard_stretching (container, event);
6044 }
6045 break;
6046 case GDK_KEY_F10:
6047 /* handle Ctrl+F10 because we want to display the
6048 * background popup even if something is selected.
6049 * The other cases are handled by popup_menu().
6050 */
6051 if (event->state & GDK_CONTROL_MASK)
6052 {
6053 handled = handle_popups (container, event,
6054 "context_click_background");
6055 }
6056 break;
6057 case GDK_KEY_v:
6058 /* Eat Control + v to not enable type ahead */
6059 if ((event->state & GDK_CONTROL_MASK) != 0)
6060 {
6061 handled = TRUE;
6062 }
6063 break;
6064 default:
6065 break;
6066 }
6067 }
6068
6069 if (!handled)
6070 {
6071 handled = GTK_WIDGET_CLASS (caja_icon_container_parent_class)->key_press_event (widget, event);
6072 }
6073
6074 /* We pass the event to the search_entry. If its text changes, then we
6075 * start the typeahead find capabilities.
6076 * Copied from CajaIconContainer */
6077 if (!handled &&
6078 event->keyval != GDK_KEY_slash /* don't steal slash key event, used for "go to" */ &&
6079 event->keyval != GDK_KEY_BackSpace &&
6080 event->keyval != GDK_KEY_Delete)
6081 {
6082 GdkEvent *new_event;
6083 GdkWindow *window;
6084 char *old_text;
6085 const char *new_text;
6086 gboolean retval;
6087 gboolean text_modified;
6088 gulong popup_menu_id;
6089
6090 caja_icon_container_ensure_interactive_directory (container);
6091
6092 /* Make a copy of the current text */
6093 old_text = g_strdup (gtk_entry_get_text (GTK_ENTRY (container->details->search_entry)));
6094 new_event = gdk_event_copy ((GdkEvent *) event);
6095 window = ((GdkEventKey *) new_event)->window;
6096 ((GdkEventKey *) new_event)->window = gtk_widget_get_window (container->details->search_entry);
6097 gtk_widget_realize (container->details->search_window);
6098
6099 popup_menu_id = g_signal_connect (container->details->search_entry,
6100 "popup_menu", G_CALLBACK (gtk_true), NULL);
6101
6102 gtk_widget_show (container->details->search_window);
6103
6104 /* Send the event to the window. If the preedit_changed signal is emitted
6105 * during this event, we will set priv->imcontext_changed */
6106 container->details->imcontext_changed = FALSE;
6107 retval = gtk_widget_event (container->details->search_entry, new_event);
6108 gtk_widget_hide (container->details->search_window);
6109
6110 g_signal_handler_disconnect (container->details->search_entry,
6111 popup_menu_id);
6112
6113 /* We check to make sure that the entry tried to handle the text, and that
6114 * the text has changed. */
6115 new_text = gtk_entry_get_text (GTK_ENTRY (container->details->search_entry));
6116 text_modified = strcmp (old_text, new_text) != 0;
6117 g_free (old_text);
6118 if (container->details->imcontext_changed || /* we're in a preedit */
6119 (retval && text_modified)) /* ...or the text was modified */
6120 {
6121 if (caja_icon_container_real_start_interactive_search (container, FALSE))
6122 {
6123 gtk_widget_grab_focus (GTK_WIDGET (container));
6124 return TRUE;
6125 }
6126 else
6127 {
6128 gtk_entry_set_text (GTK_ENTRY (container->details->search_entry), "");
6129 return FALSE;
6130 }
6131 }
6132
6133 ((GdkEventKey *) new_event)->window = window;
6134 gdk_event_free (new_event);
6135 }
6136
6137 return handled;
6138}
6139
6140static gboolean
6141popup_menu (GtkWidget *widget)
6142{
6143 CajaIconContainer *container;
6144
6145 container = CAJA_ICON_CONTAINER (widget);
6146
6147 if (has_selection (container))
6148 {
6149 handle_popups (container, NULL,
6150 "context_click_selection");
6151 }
6152 else
6153 {
6154 handle_popups (container, NULL,
6155 "context_click_background");
6156 }
6157
6158 return TRUE;
6159}
6160
6161static void
6162draw_canvas_background (EelCanvas *canvas,
6163 cairo_t *cr)
6164{
6165 /* Don't chain up to the parent to avoid clearing and redrawing */
6166}
6167
6168static void
6169grab_notify_cb (GtkWidget *widget,
6170 gboolean was_grabbed)
6171{
6172 CajaIconContainer *container;
6173
6174 container = CAJA_ICON_CONTAINER (widget);
6175
6176 if (container->details->rubberband_info.active &&
6177 !was_grabbed)
6178 {
6179 /* we got a (un)grab-notify during rubberband.
6180 * This happens when a new modal dialog shows
6181 * up (e.g. authentication or an error). Stop
6182 * the rubberbanding so that we can handle the
6183 * dialog. */
6184 stop_rubberbanding (container);
6185 }
6186}
6187
6188static void
6189text_ellipsis_limit_changed_container_callback (gpointer callback_data)
6190{
6191 CajaIconContainer *container;
6192
6193 container = CAJA_ICON_CONTAINER (callback_data);
6194 invalidate_label_sizes (container);
6195 schedule_redo_layout (container);
6196}
6197
6198static GObject*
6199caja_icon_container_constructor (GType type,
6200 guint n_construct_params,
6201 GObjectConstructParam *construct_params)
6202{
6203 CajaIconContainer *container;
6204 GObject *object;
6205
6206 object = G_OBJECT_CLASS (caja_icon_container_parent_class)->constructor
6207 (type,
6208 n_construct_params,
6209 construct_params);
6210
6211 container = CAJA_ICON_CONTAINER (object);
6212 if (caja_icon_container_get_is_desktop (container))
6213 {
6214 g_signal_connect_swapped (caja_desktop_preferences,
6215 "changed::" CAJA_PREFERENCES_DESKTOP_TEXT_ELLIPSIS_LIMIT,
6216 G_CALLBACK (text_ellipsis_limit_changed_container_callback),
6217 container);
6218 }
6219 else
6220 {
6221 g_signal_connect_swapped (caja_icon_view_preferences,
6222 "changed::" CAJA_PREFERENCES_ICON_VIEW_TEXT_ELLIPSIS_LIMIT,
6223 G_CALLBACK (text_ellipsis_limit_changed_container_callback),
6224 container);
6225 }
6226
6227 return object;
6228}

6645static void
6646update_selected (CajaIconContainer *container)
6647{
6648 GList *node;
6649 CajaIcon *icon = NULL;
6650
6651 for (node = container->details->icons; node != NULL; node = node->next)
6652 {
6653 icon = node->data;
6654 if (icon->is_selected)
6655 {
6656 eel_canvas_item_request_update (EEL_CANVAS_ITEM (icon->item));
6657 }
6658 }
6659}
6660
6661static gboolean
6662handle_focus_in_event (GtkWidget *widget, GdkEventFocus *event, gpointer user_data)
6663{
6664 update_selected (CAJA_ICON_CONTAINER (widget));
6665
6666 return FALSE;
6667}
6668
6669static gboolean
6670handle_focus_out_event (GtkWidget *widget, GdkEventFocus *event, gpointer user_data)
6671{
6672 /* End renaming and commit change. */
6673 end_renaming_mode (CAJA_ICON_CONTAINER (widget), TRUE);
6674 update_selected (CAJA_ICON_CONTAINER (widget));
6675
6676 return FALSE;
6677}
